1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:16,916
It's the beginning of the year 2026.

2
00:00:16,983 --> 00:00:18,585
Happy New Year, everyone.

3
00:00:18,651 --> 00:00:20,587
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> also welcomes

4
00:00:20,653 --> 00:00:24,357
a new beginning with the 2026 season.

5
00:00:24,424 --> 00:00:28,161
Forget the stars you've won
in the previous season.

6
00:00:28,228 --> 00:00:30,063
-Did you take them off?
-Yes.

7
00:00:30,130 --> 00:00:31,865
-This is great.
-It's a new beginning.

8
00:00:31,931 --> 00:00:33,466
I believe last year

9
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:36,202
was a bit more advantageous
to the returning chefs.

10
00:00:36,269 --> 00:00:37,837
But this year will be different.

11
00:00:37,904 --> 00:00:38,905
I'm fully adjusted now,

12
00:00:38,972 --> 00:00:40,840
and I have no other excuses to make.

13
00:00:40,907 --> 00:00:43,576
Starting this year,
I'll begin my hunt for the stars.

14
00:00:43,643 --> 00:00:45,512
For goodness' sake, start hunting.

15
00:00:45,578 --> 00:00:48,014
They're at it already. I'm sick of them.

16
00:00:48,081 --> 00:00:50,784
Let's hear from Chef Nam-no
and find out his New Year's resolution.

17
00:00:50,850 --> 00:00:52,452
In 2025,

18
00:00:52,519 --> 00:00:54,054
our good old sirs…

19
00:00:54,621 --> 00:00:56,289
GOOD OLD SIRS?

20
00:00:56,856 --> 00:00:58,425
THE GOOD OLD CANINE SIR

21
00:00:58,491 --> 00:01:00,994
-It's respectful to call someone a sir.
-Yes.

22
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:02,629
You added "good old" in front of it.

23
00:01:02,695 --> 00:01:05,565
I meant our elders,
with respect, of course.

24
00:01:05,632 --> 00:01:07,100
The elderly… No, the good old sirs.

25
00:01:07,434 --> 00:01:09,002
PISSED

26
00:01:09,069 --> 00:01:11,204
-That was offensive.
-"The elderly"?

27
00:01:11,771 --> 00:01:13,673
THE CANINE APPEARS

28
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:15,809
-He wants good old in-sir-pirations.
-The OGs.

29
00:01:15,875 --> 00:01:19,045
-I'll do my best to strobe… Strive to win.
-Of course.

30
00:01:19,112 --> 00:01:23,483
And there are a few chefs
competing in <i>Culinary Class Wars.</i>

31
00:01:23,550 --> 00:01:25,685
-They're playing key roles.
-They are.

32
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:27,454
-They've been owning it…
-Seriously.

33
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:29,389
-They're on fire!
-…dominating the show.

34
00:01:29,456 --> 00:01:32,092
Especially so for Chef Jong-won
in the beginning.

35
00:01:32,158 --> 00:01:33,259
-Man.
-Right away.

36
00:01:33,326 --> 00:01:34,861
"Can you stop me?"

37
00:01:36,629 --> 00:01:39,099
-He was frightening, very savage.
-Unlike how he is here.

38
00:01:39,165 --> 00:01:41,935
"I've also worked
at a three-star Michelin restaurant,

39
00:01:42,001 --> 00:01:44,437
but that didn't make me
a three-star chef."

40
00:01:44,504 --> 00:01:46,739
-"I have to earn the stars myself."
-That's it!

41
00:01:46,806 --> 00:01:47,907
My gosh!

42
00:01:48,641 --> 00:01:51,010
-And he raised his eyes like this.
-It was so…

43
00:01:51,077 --> 00:01:52,979
-Like this.
-I didn't know he could make that face.

44
00:01:53,046 --> 00:01:54,180
-And with a smile.
-Yes.

45
00:01:54,247 --> 00:01:56,416
-With a smile.
-He's so cool on that show.

46
00:01:56,483 --> 00:01:59,519
There must be a difference
between this show and <i>Culinary Class Wars.</i>

47
00:01:59,586 --> 00:02:02,622
Well, what I liked about
<i>Culinary Class Wars</i> was the quietness.

48
00:02:05,158 --> 00:02:06,893
AFTER ALL, IT'S VERY ROWDY HERE

49
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:09,162
<i>There are no hosts who bother you</i>
<i>or Kim Poong.</i>

50
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:10,063
NO KIM POONG

51
00:02:10,730 --> 00:02:12,832
But this show trained me well.

52
00:02:12,899 --> 00:02:14,334
People began to shout out

53
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:17,036
that we only had three minutes left,

54
00:02:17,103 --> 00:02:19,873
but I thought, "Three minutes?"

55
00:02:19,939 --> 00:02:24,410
"On <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>, that's enough time
to have a gulp of water, visit the fridge,

56
00:02:24,477 --> 00:02:26,713
and make two more dishes."

57
00:02:26,779 --> 00:02:27,780
-That's true.
-Yes.

58
00:02:27,847 --> 00:02:29,582
-That's a lot of time.
-I can make two more.

59
00:02:29,649 --> 00:02:30,884
-Of course.
-And do a final check.

60
00:02:30,950 --> 00:02:33,920
-I owe a lot to <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>
-It's tough training.

61
00:02:33,987 --> 00:02:35,655
-We made them who they are.
-Of course.

62
00:02:35,722 --> 00:02:38,825
-We tried so hard to train them.
-And tasted our food.

63
00:02:38,892 --> 00:02:41,361
Who put him at ease
although he had three minutes left?

64
00:02:41,427 --> 00:02:43,830
-It was us!
-Of course, it was us.

65
00:02:43,897 --> 00:02:47,033
-We gave you proper sandbag training!
-Of course.

66
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:50,670
-This is boot camp for you!
-Yes.

67
00:02:51,337 --> 00:02:53,540
-With a tire around my waist.
-Yes, with a tire.

68
00:02:53,606 --> 00:02:55,341
Was it helpful to have been here?

69
00:02:55,408 --> 00:02:57,744
-It was very helpful.
-Very much?

70
00:02:57,810 --> 00:02:59,279
Because I was definitely

71
00:02:59,345 --> 00:03:02,215
free from the pressure
of their time limit.

72
00:03:02,282 --> 00:03:03,883
Did you dance there as well?

73
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:05,351
HAHA

74
00:03:05,418 --> 00:03:06,553
I saw lots of comments like that.

75
00:03:06,619 --> 00:03:10,023
No one wanted to see me dance
on that show.

76
00:03:11,257 --> 00:03:13,159
We're pretty much a culinary school.

77
00:03:13,226 --> 00:03:14,994
-A culinary boot camp.
-Yes, a boot camp.

78
00:03:15,762 --> 00:03:18,097
THE 2ND CLASS STUDENTS
OF CHEF & MY FRIDGE BOOT CAMP

79
00:03:18,164 --> 00:03:19,866
Poong, get ready to join the third season.

80
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,401
Wait, me? Me?

81
00:03:21,467 --> 00:03:22,735
Yes, get ready for that show.

82
00:03:22,802 --> 00:03:24,537
-We'll make you the winner.
-Yes.

83
00:03:25,438 --> 00:03:27,840
-I'll do my best and practice.
-All right.

84
00:03:27,907 --> 00:03:32,478
We await the first guests of the year
who'll share their fridges with us.

85
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:35,748
Please welcome today's fridge owners!

86
00:03:35,815 --> 00:03:37,150
Come on out!

87
00:03:38,685 --> 00:03:41,821
The first fridge owners of the new year!

88
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:46,292
Please welcome the lovely villains,
Rhee Min-jung and Yoo Ji-tae!

89
00:03:46,359 --> 00:03:48,761
-Welcome.
-Hello.

90
00:03:49,262 --> 00:03:50,563
It's great to have you here.

91
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:52,899
WELCOME TO THE SHOW

92
00:03:52,966 --> 00:03:54,834
Her honest and down-to-earth charms

93
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:58,471
are what let her whip her husband
Lee Byung-hun to shape.

94
00:03:58,538 --> 00:04:00,106
The original goddess,
more beautiful than flowers,

95
00:04:00,173 --> 00:04:01,674
please welcome actor Rhee Min-jung!

96
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:03,810
ACTOR RHEE MIN-JUNG

97
00:04:03,876 --> 00:04:06,679
-She has such a tiny face. Seriously.
-Welcome to the show.

98
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:08,881
Allow me to introduce him too.
Doesn't he seem so cool?

99
00:04:08,948 --> 00:04:10,416
-How can your love change?
-<i>One Fine Spring Day…</i>

100
00:04:10,483 --> 00:04:11,985
Do you want some <i>ramyeon?</i>

101
00:04:12,051 --> 00:04:13,686
HIS EVER-DOMINEERING PRESENCE

102
00:04:13,753 --> 00:04:17,724
<i>…to </i>Old Boy<i>, a man with a thousand faces</i>
<i>jumping between good and evil</i>

103
00:04:17,790 --> 00:04:21,194
and a genius actor turned professor
who has been teaching lately,

104
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:23,196
please welcome our guest,
actor Yoo Ji-tae!

105
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:25,932
-Welcome to the show!
-We're here with a professor.

106
00:04:25,999 --> 00:04:27,734
WELCOME

107
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:31,004
Was there a special reason
why you two came to visit us today?

108
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:33,806
Our drama, <i>Villains</i>, recently started…

109
00:04:33,873 --> 00:04:36,676
-Oh, <i>Villains</i>.
-…so we came to promote the series.

110
00:04:36,743 --> 00:04:38,878
Which one of you is the villain, then?

111
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:40,146
-Everyone.
-Everyone is.

112
00:04:40,213 --> 00:04:41,981
-<i>Everyone</i>?
-<i>Yes, hence,</i> Villains.

113
00:04:42,048 --> 00:04:44,183
<i>That's why it's in the plural.</i>

114
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:48,888
We make a huge stash of counterfeit money.

115
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:50,456
It's confirmed as a flawless fake note.

116
00:04:50,523 --> 00:04:53,159
<i>Then we try to switch it out</i>
<i>with real money.</i>

117
00:04:53,226 --> 00:04:57,697
And which one of the villains
will end up taking the actual money?

118
00:04:58,131 --> 00:04:59,732
SHOW LOTS OF LOVE FOR THE LOVELY VILLAINS

119
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,000
That's the story.

120
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:04,070
It's a rare occasion
to see you two on a variety show.

121
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:07,674
So have you ever watched <i>Chef & My Fridge?</i>

122
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:09,776
Yes, I've watched it a few times.

123
00:05:09,842 --> 00:05:11,778
I often saw the chefs

124
00:05:11,844 --> 00:05:13,546
in quarrels.

125
00:05:13,613 --> 00:05:14,781
CALLED OUT

126
00:05:14,847 --> 00:05:15,782
Who's quarreling?

127
00:05:15,848 --> 00:05:17,450
-You two.
-Us?

128
00:05:18,017 --> 00:05:20,153
VIDEO EVIDENCE

129
00:05:20,219 --> 00:05:22,622
-Who were the ones who fought?
-Why did you quarrel?

130
00:05:22,689 --> 00:05:25,258
-And you cooked together too.
-You shouldn't fight.

131
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:27,126
It was fun to watch.

132
00:05:27,193 --> 00:05:30,330
It's like professional wrestling.
People tend to think

133
00:05:30,396 --> 00:05:32,699
we're really fighting each other,

134
00:05:32,765 --> 00:05:36,069
but we're just bickering
with one another as a part of the show.

135
00:05:36,135 --> 00:05:38,271
It's just something that we do.

136
00:05:38,338 --> 00:05:41,374
HE SUDDENLY WANTED
TO STRAIGHTEN HIS KNIVES, THAT'S ALL

137
00:05:41,441 --> 00:05:45,445
Min-jung, I heard
you came today in excitement.

138
00:05:45,511 --> 00:05:48,181
I'm someone who cooks at home,

139
00:05:48,247 --> 00:05:51,951
so I'm quite sick and tired
of making food.

140
00:05:52,719 --> 00:05:54,220
-I see.
-I heard they'd cook for me,

141
00:05:54,287 --> 00:05:55,555
so I came gladly and at ease.

142
00:05:55,621 --> 00:05:57,123
-It must be tough.
-I get it.

143
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:58,291
But I heard your son

144
00:05:58,358 --> 00:06:01,160
was more excited to see you on the show,
even more than you.

145
00:06:01,227 --> 00:06:02,528
-Yes.
-Really?

146
00:06:02,595 --> 00:06:04,831
-Your 11-year-old son?
-And the reason

147
00:06:04,897 --> 00:06:06,866
-sits right here.
-I see.

148
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:09,802
-Me?
-We're actually neighbors.

149
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:11,671
-You are?
-Yes.

150
00:06:11,738 --> 00:06:14,040
-But I've never seen him around.
-I haven't either.

151
00:06:14,107 --> 00:06:17,043
-Jun-hu played soccer for a long time…
-I hear he loves soccer.

152
00:06:17,110 --> 00:06:19,779
…so whenever he played
with his friends in the neighborhood,

153
00:06:19,846 --> 00:06:22,782
he wondered,
"Maybe Mr. Ahn will come down."

154
00:06:22,849 --> 00:06:25,118
He once suggested that they
shout out your name, and they did.

155
00:06:25,184 --> 00:06:27,320
-"Ahn Jung-hwan!" Like this?
-Yes!

156
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:29,989
"Ahn Jung-hwan! Show yourself!"

157
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:32,258
They'd go, "Come and play with us!"

158
00:06:32,325 --> 00:06:35,194
I had to shush them and remind them
that people are trying to rest.

159
00:06:35,261 --> 00:06:37,463
When I saw Byung-hun,
he mentioned that his son liked me

160
00:06:37,530 --> 00:06:39,732
-and brought a ball for me to sign.
-Yes.

161
00:06:39,799 --> 00:06:43,035
I took it and signed it already,
but I haven't had a chance to return it.

162
00:06:43,102 --> 00:06:46,639
If you leave it out in the garden
on the first floor, I'll pick it up.

163
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:49,575
She came ready to get what she needed.

164
00:06:49,642 --> 00:06:51,444
-Show yourself to the kids.
-She did.

165
00:06:51,511 --> 00:06:53,946
So that was why. For the first time,

166
00:06:54,013 --> 00:06:55,581
I saw the <i>Chef & My Fridge </i>box truck.

167
00:06:55,648 --> 00:06:57,417
-Did we take the fridge yesterday?
-Yes.

168
00:06:57,483 --> 00:06:58,751
A-HA

169
00:06:58,818 --> 00:07:00,119
-In the afternoon, right?
-Yes.

170
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:02,588
Yes, he'd even notice that,
but we had never met.

171
00:07:02,655 --> 00:07:04,023
It was my first time seeing it.

172
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,758
I thought, "So it wasn't a lie."

173
00:07:05,825 --> 00:07:07,326
We really take it the day before.

174
00:07:07,393 --> 00:07:12,265
Min-jung had quite a busy year
for her career in 2025, the last year.

175
00:07:12,331 --> 00:07:14,967
Her YouTube channel
must be the hottest among them.

176
00:07:15,034 --> 00:07:16,302
<i>Yes, she started a channel.</i>

177
00:07:16,369 --> 00:07:17,804
<i>She came across a goddess before,</i>

178
00:07:17,870 --> 00:07:20,339
<i>but that helped her build</i>
<i>a friendlier and laid-back image.</i>

179
00:07:20,406 --> 00:07:22,275
I watch her channel often,

180
00:07:22,341 --> 00:07:25,711
-but Byung-hun is always blurred out.
-Yes.

181
00:07:25,778 --> 00:07:26,646
It's hilarious.

182
00:07:26,712 --> 00:07:30,149
I had to make a pledge
as soon as I started, and I…

183
00:07:30,216 --> 00:07:32,318
Once I hit 500,000 subscribers,

184
00:07:32,385 --> 00:07:34,887
I'll invite Lee Byung-hun
and Director Park Chan-wook.

185
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,622
I pledged to invite them both.

186
00:07:36,689 --> 00:07:39,392
I said it myself,

187
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,894
so I couldn't keep showing him
in the videos.

188
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:45,164
<i>I had to blur him out</i>
<i>every time he was in the footage.</i>

189
00:07:45,231 --> 00:07:46,866
HE-WHO-MUST-NOT-BE-SHOWN
BEFORE SHE HITS 500K

190
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:48,701
So that was the reason.

191
00:07:48,768 --> 00:07:52,038
Also, the closer I got
to 500,000 subscribers,

192
00:07:52,104 --> 00:07:54,507
the blur became more subtle.

193
00:07:54,574 --> 00:07:55,708
-Gradually?
-And then

194
00:07:55,775 --> 00:07:57,477
people began to comment, "Is it just me?"

195
00:07:57,543 --> 00:07:59,779
"The blur became softer, right?"

196
00:07:59,846 --> 00:08:02,615
So I replied and said they were right,
that it was becoming softer.

197
00:08:02,682 --> 00:08:06,118
About two weeks ago,

198
00:08:06,185 --> 00:08:08,454
-I reached 500,000 subscribers.
-You did?

199
00:08:08,521 --> 00:08:11,057
So he sent me a video.

200
00:08:11,123 --> 00:08:13,726
Congratulations on hitting
500,000 subscribers.

201
00:08:13,793 --> 00:08:16,762
I'm not blurred out anymore, so…

202
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,564
But he filmed himself way too close,

203
00:08:18,631 --> 00:08:21,334
so people thought he was too much
and wanted him blurred out again.

204
00:08:21,801 --> 00:08:23,169
THEY CAN'T GET USED TO THE RAZOR-SHARP BH

205
00:08:23,236 --> 00:08:24,136
A sudden tone shift.

206
00:08:24,203 --> 00:08:25,771
"Go back to the way it was."

207
00:08:25,838 --> 00:08:28,407
I thought, "Why did he film himself
so up close?"

208
00:08:28,474 --> 00:08:30,243
But that's what the subscribers love.

209
00:08:30,309 --> 00:08:32,345
-That's the fun.
-It's fun.

210
00:08:32,411 --> 00:08:36,048
But the content that actually gave you
a big break is something else.

211
00:08:36,115 --> 00:08:39,185
-Min-jung's Home-Cooked Meals?
-Min-jung's Home-Cooked Meals?

212
00:08:39,252 --> 00:08:42,154
I like to whip up something
with whatever I have in the fridge,

213
00:08:42,221 --> 00:08:44,724
so it's highly efficient
and easy to make if you have a stove.

214
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:46,526
I guess people love that content

215
00:08:46,592 --> 00:08:48,060
because that's how I like to cook.

216
00:08:48,594 --> 00:08:49,595
A-HA

217
00:08:49,662 --> 00:08:51,430
Let us show you a couple of pictures.

218
00:08:51,497 --> 00:08:53,933
Let's find out how good a cook she is.

219
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,868
SURPRISED

220
00:08:56,269 --> 00:08:57,603
WHOAAAA

221
00:08:58,037 --> 00:08:59,071
WHOA-HUH?

222
00:08:59,138 --> 00:09:00,973
Let's find out how good a cook she is.

223
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:03,676
LIKE A FINE DINING RESTAURANT

224
00:09:03,743 --> 00:09:06,512
-Mimosa eggs topped with caviar.
-These look amazing.

225
00:09:06,579 --> 00:09:07,580
-How did she…
-Did she…

226
00:09:07,647 --> 00:09:08,948
ANOTHER SET OF PHOTOS

227
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:12,251
Do you usually eat like this?

228
00:09:12,318 --> 00:09:13,986
-Have you learned?
-It's the presentation.

229
00:09:14,053 --> 00:09:15,254
No, I've never learned to cook.

230
00:09:15,321 --> 00:09:17,456
-You taught yourself?
-Yes.

231
00:09:17,523 --> 00:09:20,426
I see why she has content
called Min-jung's Home-Cooked Meals.

232
00:09:20,493 --> 00:09:21,694
Don't call her just Min-jung.

233
00:09:21,761 --> 00:09:24,130
It's Chef Min-jung's Home-Cooked Meals.

234
00:09:24,196 --> 00:09:25,031
TRUE!

235
00:09:25,097 --> 00:09:27,533
If you allow me some time,

236
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:31,671
I can also whip up something
as quickly as the chefs here.

237
00:09:32,438 --> 00:09:33,539
That's the case now, anyway.

238
00:09:33,606 --> 00:09:36,375
Raising two kids is a whole new level
compared to just one.

239
00:09:36,442 --> 00:09:38,711
-I didn't expect this at all.
-You're right.

240
00:09:38,778 --> 00:09:40,680
Let's say it's <i>jang-jorim,</i>
a braised side dish.

241
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:42,014
I throw everything into a pot

242
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:43,716
and take a shower while it boils down.

243
00:09:43,783 --> 00:09:46,552
I shower, come out,
taste it, and get it ready to eat.

244
00:09:46,619 --> 00:09:48,454
-While it's on the stove?
-Yes.

245
00:09:48,521 --> 00:09:51,624
I turn the heat down, so it boils
over medium heat after boiling hard.

246
00:09:51,691 --> 00:09:53,859
I hope one of her orders is,

247
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:56,228
"Cook for Eight Minutes
and Use the Rest to Shower."

248
00:09:56,662 --> 00:09:58,931
I'D LIKE A DISH I CAN MAKE
WHILE TAKING A SHOWER

249
00:09:58,998 --> 00:10:01,400
-And drying my hair and putting makeup on.
-She must do everything.

250
00:10:01,467 --> 00:10:02,802
-That's funny.
-While the food boils.

251
00:10:02,868 --> 00:10:04,971
Even a great cook like her

252
00:10:05,037 --> 00:10:08,774
once fought with her husband
because of food.

253
00:10:08,841 --> 00:10:11,177
-Is he not pleased?
-That's impossible.

254
00:10:11,243 --> 00:10:12,645
While we were still newlyweds,

255
00:10:12,712 --> 00:10:13,980
I even cried over the matter.

256
00:10:14,046 --> 00:10:15,982
-Were you disappointed?
-Yes.

257
00:10:16,048 --> 00:10:17,550
When you're still newlyweds,

258
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:19,619
you want to put in extra work, right?

259
00:10:19,685 --> 00:10:22,521
Let's say I make dishes
like <i>jeon, namul</i>, and soup.

260
00:10:22,588 --> 00:10:25,524
But he'll finish everything
before I bring him the soup.

261
00:10:25,591 --> 00:10:27,560
-I get it.
-I think I get it.

262
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:29,028
-Men do that.
-He's a quick eater.

263
00:10:29,095 --> 00:10:30,229
We stash the food in.

264
00:10:30,296 --> 00:10:32,498
He always finishes eating
within five minutes.

265
00:10:32,565 --> 00:10:33,733
-Five minutes?
-It's disappointing.

266
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:35,501
-Of course.
-I haven't even had a bite.

267
00:10:35,568 --> 00:10:37,003
-I get it.
-But because he lived

268
00:10:37,069 --> 00:10:39,972
over 30 years on set as an actor,

269
00:10:40,039 --> 00:10:42,074
he had a habit
of eating quickly to get ready.

270
00:10:42,541 --> 00:10:43,609
THAT'S HOW IT IS

271
00:10:43,676 --> 00:10:45,745
He doesn't eat as quickly anymore,

272
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:47,413
but it's still only about ten minutes.

273
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,649
-Ten minutes? Yes, twice.
-That's twice as much.

274
00:10:49,715 --> 00:10:51,617
He can now shake his leg
and wait for his soup.

275
00:10:51,684 --> 00:10:54,086
Even after he gets the soup,

276
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:56,088
he tries to eat slowly
while shaking his leg,

277
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:58,424
then, when I take a seat, he digs in.

278
00:10:58,491 --> 00:10:59,759
It makes us nervous to eat slowly.

279
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:01,093
That's about ten minutes now.

280
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:03,462
And I've become faster at eating, so…

281
00:11:03,529 --> 00:11:05,331
-Your pace?
-Yes, so our speed is about the same now.

282
00:11:05,398 --> 00:11:07,633
My family is similar to hers.
I'm a very quick eater too.

283
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,035
-You are?
-I am.

284
00:11:09,101 --> 00:11:10,202
Let's find out

285
00:11:10,269 --> 00:11:14,573
the ingredients Min-jung has in the fridge
as the master of home cooking.

286
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:17,043
Can we look forward to opening it?

287
00:11:17,109 --> 00:11:19,245
I keep lots of ingredients in stock,

288
00:11:19,311 --> 00:11:21,714
so I'm sure they'll have
a good amount to work with.

289
00:11:21,781 --> 00:11:22,782
AN ABUNDANCE OF INGREDIENTS

290
00:11:23,282 --> 00:11:25,685
What did your family say
when we took your fridge?

291
00:11:25,751 --> 00:11:28,154
"What are we going to eat
if they take everything?"

292
00:11:28,220 --> 00:11:29,355
HAHAHAHAHA

293
00:11:29,422 --> 00:11:31,791
You didn't take everything, though.

294
00:11:31,857 --> 00:11:34,293
They let us keep some eggs.

295
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,828
It's because we have eggs here.

296
00:11:35,895 --> 00:11:38,898
This is the first fridge we see in 2026.

297
00:11:38,964 --> 00:11:40,966
-We present Min-jung's fridge!
-Fridge!

298
00:11:41,834 --> 00:11:43,736
OH MY

299
00:11:43,803 --> 00:11:44,937
-…Fridge!
-Fridge!

300
00:11:45,004 --> 00:11:47,039
PRESENTING RHEE MIN-JUNG'S FRIDGE

301
00:11:47,306 --> 00:11:48,474
ALREADY MAKING YOU FEEL FULL

302
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:49,709
-That's a lot.
-It's full.

303
00:11:49,775 --> 00:11:51,844
Let us begin with the top shelf.

304
00:11:51,911 --> 00:11:53,579
I see some soy milk. Soybean soup.

305
00:11:53,646 --> 00:11:56,115
In the days before an awards show,

306
00:11:56,182 --> 00:11:58,684
I tried drinking
black soy milk for dinner.

307
00:11:58,751 --> 00:12:00,019
INTERESTED

308
00:12:00,086 --> 00:12:03,322
-So you drink this to watch your shape?
-Soybean soup?

309
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:07,359
Also, I hear soybeans
are good for women as we age.

310
00:12:07,426 --> 00:12:10,062
I see some <i>gomtang, </i>beef bone broth.

311
00:12:10,129 --> 00:12:11,564
Who eats this?

312
00:12:11,630 --> 00:12:15,267
I used to make my own beef bone broth,

313
00:12:15,334 --> 00:12:18,437
but I don't have enough time
to do that now.

314
00:12:18,504 --> 00:12:21,807
So when I make something
with bone broth, I just throw those in.

315
00:12:22,641 --> 00:12:23,642
I SEE

316
00:12:23,709 --> 00:12:25,945
-Your husband, son, and everyone love it?
-Yes.

317
00:12:26,812 --> 00:12:30,282
Is there anything else you make
that everyone in the family enjoys?

318
00:12:30,349 --> 00:12:32,084
-I'd say curry.
-Curry.

319
00:12:32,151 --> 00:12:34,820
-Everyone loves curry, so yes.
-Yes.

320
00:12:34,887 --> 00:12:37,189
You have to think about these things
with a bigger family.

321
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:38,624
One shot, two birds.

322
00:12:38,691 --> 00:12:40,526
-One shot, two birds.
-She gets technical. One shot, two birds.

323
00:12:40,593 --> 00:12:41,594
One shot, two birds?

324
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:43,129
LOVES IT

325
00:12:43,195 --> 00:12:44,597
One shot, four birds.

326
00:12:44,663 --> 00:12:46,799
I see some side dishes
on the second shelf.

327
00:12:46,866 --> 00:12:49,502
-Kimchi from Jeolla-do, radish kimchi,
-Kimchi from Jeolla-do?

328
00:12:49,568 --> 00:12:51,470
and this <i>mukeunji</i> is three years old.

329
00:12:51,537 --> 00:12:55,775
I have to use different kimchi
when I braise them or stew them,

330
00:12:55,841 --> 00:12:57,376
depending on the fermentation.

331
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:59,845
Who made this three-year-old <i>mukeunji?</i>

332
00:12:59,912 --> 00:13:01,580
My mother-in-law.

333
00:13:02,915 --> 00:13:05,718
I make kimchi gimbap with her <i>mukeunji.</i>

334
00:13:05,785 --> 00:13:07,253
-Kimchi gimbap?
-Yes, kimchi gimbap.

335
00:13:07,319 --> 00:13:10,222
Mix the kimchi
with perilla oil, and sesame,

336
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:12,024
-then wring it out.
-That sounds good.

337
00:13:12,091 --> 00:13:15,895
Then I add cheese and Spam
to make kimchi <i>gimbap.</i>

338
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:18,898
I once brought about 30 servings
to Byung-hun's set,

339
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:21,801
and the director suggested
that we start a business with it.

340
00:13:22,835 --> 00:13:24,436
-With kimchi gimbap?
-It sounds good.

341
00:13:24,503 --> 00:13:26,539
It was that good.

342
00:13:26,605 --> 00:13:28,474
-I want to try some.
-Right?

343
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:31,277
Another shelf down, I see some meat.

344
00:13:31,343 --> 00:13:33,712
Pork neck, and probably pork belly.

345
00:13:33,779 --> 00:13:36,782
I use thinly sliced pork belly
when I have to whip up something,

346
00:13:36,849 --> 00:13:39,185
and I make spicy stir-fried pork
for my husband.

347
00:13:39,251 --> 00:13:41,187
He must like <i>jeyuk-bokkeum.</i>

348
00:13:41,253 --> 00:13:42,955
He likes spicy food.

349
00:13:43,022 --> 00:13:46,158
-Like <i>osam-</i>bulgogi and <i>jeyuk-bokkeum.</i>
-He likes spicy food.

350
00:13:46,225 --> 00:13:47,760
Do you also enjoy <i>jeyuk-bokkeum?</i>

351
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:51,330
I actually prefer meat without any sauce.

352
00:13:51,397 --> 00:13:53,632
I like to eat a nice cut of beef

353
00:13:53,699 --> 00:13:56,869
with a bit of wasabi or good salt

354
00:13:56,936 --> 00:13:58,637
and enjoying it as is.

355
00:13:58,704 --> 00:14:00,706
Are these <i>makgeolli?</i>

356
00:14:00,773 --> 00:14:04,109
-Yes, it's made with red rice.
-Red rice?

357
00:14:04,176 --> 00:14:05,978
-Red rice <i>makgeolli.</i>
-I thought it was strawberry milk wine.

358
00:14:06,045 --> 00:14:08,113
That's why when you drink that,

359
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:09,181
you can fool people.

360
00:14:09,248 --> 00:14:11,917
It looks like
you're drinking strawberry milk.

361
00:14:11,984 --> 00:14:13,953
Who are you trying to deceive?

362
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:16,422
My daughter began to speak now,

363
00:14:16,488 --> 00:14:18,424
and she points
to the wine bottles and says, "Mommy's!"

364
00:14:18,891 --> 00:14:20,459
A WELL-MEANT MAKGEOLLI TO FOOL HER

365
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:21,527
It was a bit awkward.

366
00:14:21,594 --> 00:14:24,763
Do you two often drink at home?

367
00:14:24,830 --> 00:14:28,267
Yes, we eat too quickly,
so we can't talk over meals,

368
00:14:28,334 --> 00:14:29,935
but he sits around for a long time

369
00:14:30,002 --> 00:14:31,537
-when he drinks.
-He sits there?

370
00:14:32,104 --> 00:14:33,739
EAT QUICKLY, DRINK SLOWLY

371
00:14:33,806 --> 00:14:35,407
What do you eat with your drinks?

372
00:14:35,474 --> 00:14:37,109
He maintains a low-sodium diet,

373
00:14:37,176 --> 00:14:38,811
but he still enjoys dried young pollack.

374
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:41,080
-That's salty.
-His bar snack preference may differ.

375
00:14:41,146 --> 00:14:42,982
Do you often eat <i>jeon,</i> fritters,
as a bar snack?

376
00:14:43,048 --> 00:14:45,618
Yes, so I'm often called Rhee Min-jeon.

377
00:14:45,684 --> 00:14:47,586
-Rhee Min-jeon.
-You love it that much?

378
00:14:47,653 --> 00:14:50,256
I like to shred zucchini
to turn them into <i>jeon,</i>

379
00:14:50,322 --> 00:14:54,059
and for potato <i>jeon, </i>it's so delicious
when you top it with some cheese

380
00:14:54,126 --> 00:14:56,829
-and melt it, so I love them all.
-On potato <i>jeon?</i>

381
00:14:56,896 --> 00:15:00,065
-She doesn't forget the details.
-Yes, even for a dish like <i>jeon.</i>

382
00:15:00,132 --> 00:15:02,601
<i>Jeon</i> is something I particularly love.

383
00:15:02,668 --> 00:15:04,203
Should we make <i>jeon?</i>

384
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:06,739
-And the next shelf.
-That's why she has lots of cheese.

385
00:15:06,805 --> 00:15:08,674
I see lots of cheese on this shelf.

386
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:10,509
And that's pasta sauce.

387
00:15:10,576 --> 00:15:12,311
Is this shelf for Western food?

388
00:15:12,378 --> 00:15:14,713
I like creamy dishes,

389
00:15:14,780 --> 00:15:18,984
so I love Western dishes like potato soup,
made with a delicious recipe.

390
00:15:19,051 --> 00:15:21,086
But I'm the only one who likes that,

391
00:15:21,620 --> 00:15:23,856
so I rarely ever make it.

392
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:28,260
I often made Western cuisine
when I was newly married,

393
00:15:28,327 --> 00:15:32,064
but when I made sandwiches or soup,
he'd finish it and say,

394
00:15:32,131 --> 00:15:33,265
"That was so good,

395
00:15:33,332 --> 00:15:35,501
but now, it's time for a meal."

396
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:37,169
IT'S JUST A SNACK
TO A KOREAN CUISINE LOVER

397
00:15:37,236 --> 00:15:38,904
-That's why I stopped.
-You have to make more.

398
00:15:38,971 --> 00:15:40,005
He doesn't care for it.

399
00:15:40,072 --> 00:15:43,676
I like to taste different kinds of dishes,

400
00:15:43,742 --> 00:15:46,779
but my husband is someone
who likes a single hearty dish.

401
00:15:46,845 --> 00:15:48,714
Like a dish of braised short ribs

402
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:50,749
or <i>osam-</i>bulgogi<i>, </i>squid and beef bulgogi<i>.</i>

403
00:15:50,816 --> 00:15:51,951
CLEARLY DIFFERENT APPETITES

404
00:15:52,017 --> 00:15:53,686
-Isn't that what men love?
-He must've grumbled a lot.

405
00:15:53,752 --> 00:15:55,387
And the crisper drawer.

406
00:15:55,454 --> 00:15:58,791
-Cabbage, zucchini, potato.
-Zucchini, potato.

407
00:15:58,857 --> 00:16:00,793
And some fruits.

408
00:16:00,859 --> 00:16:02,194
Moving on to the freezer.

409
00:16:02,261 --> 00:16:05,397
The top two shelves are full of meat.

410
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:07,166
Are these all beef?

411
00:16:07,232 --> 00:16:08,968
Yes, because my son is growing,

412
00:16:09,034 --> 00:16:11,403
-and he requires lots of meat.
-Boys eat a lot.

413
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,172
That's when kids eat the most.

414
00:16:13,238 --> 00:16:15,741
And the one below has seafood.

415
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:17,309
I often use shrimp.

416
00:16:17,376 --> 00:16:18,444
She often uses shrimp.

417
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:19,611
I see anchovies too.

418
00:16:19,678 --> 00:16:20,579
Look at these.

419
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:22,247
-I saw those in the photos.
-Lobster tails.

420
00:16:22,314 --> 00:16:25,584
-She has lobster?
-She has just about everything.

421
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:28,721
Do not worry about the ingredients
in the first fridge of 2026.

422
00:16:28,787 --> 00:16:30,055
The ingredients look great.

423
00:16:30,122 --> 00:16:32,257
That's all for Min-jung's fridge!

424
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:34,994
DONE CHECKING OUT MIN-JUNG'S FRIDGE

425
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:39,865
I wonder what she's going to order
from our chefs today.

426
00:16:39,932 --> 00:16:40,766
Please show us!

427
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,067
What is it?

428
00:16:42,134 --> 00:16:44,103
-A Course Meal With Soup…
-Soup.

429
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:45,404
-…Just for MJ.
-Oh, soup.

430
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:46,472
Soup sounds good.

431
00:16:46,538 --> 00:16:49,074
When you eat a course meal,

432
00:16:49,141 --> 00:16:53,345
you're often served with an appetizer
and soup to begin everything, right?

433
00:16:53,412 --> 00:16:56,081
So I want to start with that,
go to the next dish,

434
00:16:56,148 --> 00:16:58,584
have a refresher, and a dessert.

435
00:16:58,650 --> 00:17:00,486
A full-course meal.

436
00:17:00,552 --> 00:17:02,621
I'm not allowed
to ask for everything, am I?

437
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:04,790
No, you can ask for anything.

438
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:08,394
-Really?
-But I'm not sure if anyone will take it.

439
00:17:08,994 --> 00:17:11,230
-They'll make it happen.
-They will. Someone will.

440
00:17:11,296 --> 00:17:12,664
You'll get four to five dishes.

441
00:17:12,731 --> 00:17:14,233
-Up to five.
-We should make at least ten.

442
00:17:14,299 --> 00:17:17,436
So you want a full-course meal

443
00:17:17,503 --> 00:17:20,305
-that includes soup, right?
-Yes.

444
00:17:20,372 --> 00:17:21,807
Here's the second order.

445
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:22,975
What is it?

446
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:25,544
A Dish for All Four MJ

447
00:17:25,611 --> 00:17:27,546
-and BH Family.
-For all four?

448
00:17:27,613 --> 00:17:29,114
-I see.
-Even their kids.

449
00:17:29,181 --> 00:17:31,784
The orders are way too tough.

450
00:17:31,850 --> 00:17:33,619
As I mentioned before,

451
00:17:33,685 --> 00:17:37,289
a dish like curry
is something the entire family can enjoy.

452
00:17:37,356 --> 00:17:39,858
I want to learn to make
another dish like that.

453
00:17:39,925 --> 00:17:41,160
CAPTURE THE FAMILY'S TASTE!

454
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:43,128
-For all four.
-The entire family.

455
00:17:43,195 --> 00:17:45,164
-The husband loves Korean cuisine,
-Yes.

456
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:46,999
-but the wife, Western cuisine.
-Western cuisine.

457
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:49,601
It seems like her son loves both,

458
00:17:49,668 --> 00:17:51,570
-Yes.
-but your youngest just began to eat

459
00:17:51,637 --> 00:17:52,538
regular food, right?

460
00:17:52,604 --> 00:17:54,006
-She just began, right?
-She did.

461
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:56,442
-So it can't taste too strong.
-Right.

462
00:17:56,508 --> 00:17:59,044
Sam Kim and Son Jong-won will make
the course meal with soup,

463
00:17:59,111 --> 00:18:01,180
while Kim Poong and Jung Ho-young
will cook for the family.

464
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:02,247
All right.

465
00:18:02,314 --> 00:18:05,117
This is the first round of 2026.

466
00:18:05,184 --> 00:18:09,021
Coming right up,
A Course Meal With Soup Just for MJ!

467
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:10,322
Let us begin!

468
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:15,294
This is the first round of cook-off

469
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,296
played with ingredients
from Min-jung's fridge.

470
00:18:17,362 --> 00:18:21,266
The current kind-hearted chef of the show,
Chef Son Jong-won,

471
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:24,002
versus the once kind-hearted chef
of the show, Chef Sam Kim.

472
00:18:24,069 --> 00:18:27,339
The two are up against each other.

473
00:18:27,406 --> 00:18:29,775
-This is the opening game.
-The opening game.

474
00:18:29,842 --> 00:18:32,244
The once kind-hearted chef, Chef Saint,

475
