-Yes, capers and an anchovy.

722
00:27:55,140 --> 00:27:57,409
Wow. Look at the way he chops.

723
00:27:57,475 --> 00:27:59,010
Wow.

724
00:27:59,577 --> 00:28:00,779
SALT, PEPPER

725
00:28:00,845 --> 00:28:02,280
COOKING WINE, OLIVE OIL

726
00:28:02,347 --> 00:28:04,549
He's dead serious today.

727
00:28:04,616 --> 00:28:05,850
After all, he brought a dish.

728
00:28:05,917 --> 00:28:07,152
-He did.
-It means he's serious.

729
00:28:07,218 --> 00:28:08,219
He'll change this year.

730
00:28:08,286 --> 00:28:10,422
Wait, look at him.

731
00:28:10,488 --> 00:28:12,457
What's that pan, Chef Jong-won?

732
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:15,026
It's a pancake pan,
but I don't know what he'll do with that.

733
00:28:15,093 --> 00:28:16,227
-For his dessert?
-I wonder.

734
00:28:16,294 --> 00:28:18,129
I wonder what he'll use that for.

735
00:28:18,196 --> 00:28:19,464
What's that?

736
00:28:19,531 --> 00:28:20,532
He's making batter.

737
00:28:20,598 --> 00:28:23,401
Min-jung previously said
she liked <i>jeon</i>, so…

738
00:28:24,169 --> 00:28:25,737
EVEN MORE MOVED THAN MIN-JUNG

739
00:28:25,804 --> 00:28:27,105
-To make it pretty.
-That's amazing.

740
00:28:27,172 --> 00:28:28,940
I'm making <i>jeon</i>, the French tuile…

741
00:28:29,007 --> 00:28:31,209
-I'm making tuile, the French <i>jeon.</i>
-He got them confused.

742
00:28:31,276 --> 00:28:33,178
-Don't be nervous.
-Tuile is already French.

743
00:28:33,244 --> 00:28:34,212
He's making French <i>jeon.</i>

744
00:28:34,279 --> 00:28:35,680
-I said it backwards.
-That explains the oil.

745
00:28:35,747 --> 00:28:38,116
-I said it backwards.
-He'll make it into <i>jeon</i> shape.

746
00:28:38,183 --> 00:28:39,818
-That'll look cute.
-Wow.

747
00:28:39,884 --> 00:28:41,019
In there?

748
00:28:41,086 --> 00:28:42,754
SPRITZING THE TUILE BATTER

749
00:28:42,821 --> 00:28:44,456
That's how he's using that.

750
00:28:44,522 --> 00:28:46,291
What's in that liquid?

751
00:28:46,357 --> 00:28:48,526
-I used flour…
-Water, flour, and oil.

752
00:28:48,593 --> 00:28:49,728
Oil and water don't mix,

753
00:28:49,794 --> 00:28:50,795
so you can see bubbles.

754
00:28:50,862 --> 00:28:52,363
THE BATTER CREATES BUBBLES AND HOLES

755
00:28:52,430 --> 00:28:54,299
-And that's why you wrote a book!
-Of course.

756
00:28:54,365 --> 00:28:55,834
Yes, I'm an author now.

757
00:28:55,900 --> 00:28:57,168
He's a scholar.

758
00:28:57,235 --> 00:28:59,137
-He's sprinkling sesame seeds.
-Sesame.

759
00:28:59,671 --> 00:29:01,072
FOR THE PRESENTATION AND TEXTURE

760
00:29:01,139 --> 00:29:02,107
It's just like <i>jeon.</i>

761
00:29:02,173 --> 00:29:04,976
-It's the French sesame <i>jeon.</i>
-Sesame <i>jeon.</i>

762
00:29:05,043 --> 00:29:06,978
The man who cooks
both French and Korean cuisine.

763
00:29:07,045 --> 00:29:09,581
-I see.
-The biggest star chef in Korea.

764
00:29:09,647 --> 00:29:11,916
You were on Eun-yeong's side last week.

765
00:29:11,983 --> 00:29:12,984
I'm jumping ship.

766
00:29:13,051 --> 00:29:14,819
He's the hottest these days.

767
00:29:14,886 --> 00:29:16,554
Are the potatoes done?

768
00:29:16,621 --> 00:29:17,622
SAM GETS THE POTATOES OUT

769
00:29:17,689 --> 00:29:18,790
Isn't it hot? It looks hot.

770
00:29:18,857 --> 00:29:19,858
It is.

771
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:22,127
-It must be hot.
-It looks hot!

772
00:29:22,193 --> 00:29:23,394
Potatoes.

773
00:29:23,461 --> 00:29:25,530
He must've used the right amount of milk.

774
00:29:26,664 --> 00:29:27,932
He mixed the steamed potatoes

775
00:29:27,999 --> 00:29:30,435
with the stir-fried potatoes
and ground everything.

776
00:29:30,502 --> 00:29:32,837
-Are you grinding cheese?
-It's cheese.

777
00:29:32,904 --> 00:29:34,572
He's adding butter and milk

778
00:29:34,639 --> 00:29:36,274
to add creaminess.

779
00:29:36,341 --> 00:29:38,943
BACK INTO THE PAN AND BOIL WITH MILK

780
00:29:39,477 --> 00:29:40,812
WHAT'S JONG-WON DOING NEXT?

781
00:29:40,879 --> 00:29:43,047
-It must be strawberry jam and mascarpone.
-I see.

782
00:29:43,114 --> 00:29:45,917
I mixed cream cheese with strawberry jam.

783
00:29:45,984 --> 00:29:46,985
That looks good.

784
00:29:47,619 --> 00:29:48,620
AMAZED FOR THE NTH TIME

785
00:29:48,686 --> 00:29:50,722
STRAWBERRY JAM, MILK
STRAWBERRY SOUP BASE!

786
00:29:50,789 --> 00:29:52,457
It's the strawberry season,
so I'll add them.

787
00:29:52,524 --> 00:29:53,491
ADDING FRESH STRAWBERRIES

788
00:29:53,558 --> 00:29:54,993
How sweet of you.

789
00:29:55,059 --> 00:29:57,362
PUTTING IN HIS TWO CENTS
IN AN ANNOYING TONE

790
00:29:58,563 --> 00:29:59,764
How sweet of you.

791
00:29:59,831 --> 00:30:04,335
My daughter loves strawberries,
so we always keep some at home.

792
00:30:04,402 --> 00:30:06,037
Hurry up. There isn't much time left.

793
00:30:06,104 --> 00:30:07,438
What did he put in there?

794
00:30:07,505 --> 00:30:10,208
Potato, cabbage, and bacon.

795
00:30:10,275 --> 00:30:11,376
The potage.

796
00:30:11,442 --> 00:30:15,580
5. MIX BUTTER, SALT, AND PARMESAN
WITH THE POTAGE AND BLEND

797
00:30:17,282 --> 00:30:20,018
If you whip butter and milk,
it turns out like cream.

798
00:30:20,585 --> 00:30:22,987
You have six minutes left.

799
00:30:23,521 --> 00:30:25,290
GRILLED ZUCCHINI, OUT

800
00:30:25,857 --> 00:30:28,159
CHOPPING TUNA INTO BITE-SIZE PIECES

801
00:30:28,827 --> 00:30:33,431
5. MIX TUNA WITH SOY SAUCE,
SESAME OIL, GROUND PEPPER, AND SALT

802
00:30:33,998 --> 00:30:36,367
PILE GRILLED ZUCCHINI PIECES

803
00:30:36,434 --> 00:30:40,305
Chef Sam is using the zucchini
to roll up the marinated tuna.

804
00:30:40,371 --> 00:30:41,906
With grilled zucchini.

805
00:30:41,973 --> 00:30:44,142
-That must be the appetizer.
-Wow.

806
00:30:44,209 --> 00:30:46,110
-Wow.
-It looks good.

807
00:30:46,177 --> 00:30:48,880
-I should've done that long ago.
-Wow.

808
00:30:48,947 --> 00:30:50,982
She says she should have eaten tuna
just like that!

809
00:30:51,049 --> 00:30:52,584
Those are the fridge owner's words.

810
00:30:52,650 --> 00:30:53,685
Five minutes.

811
00:30:53,751 --> 00:30:55,186
-Five minutes.
-Five minutes.

812
00:30:55,253 --> 00:30:56,387
Five minutes.

813
00:30:56,454 --> 00:30:57,689
-Sung-ju.
-Yes?

814
00:30:57,755 --> 00:30:59,157
Please report from the kitchen.

815
00:30:59,224 --> 00:31:01,259
They're short on time

816
00:31:01,326 --> 00:31:03,561
because they're making course meals today.

817
00:31:03,628 --> 00:31:05,463
What's the situation here?

818
00:31:05,530 --> 00:31:07,298
He's grinding something here.

819
00:31:07,365 --> 00:31:08,633
What are you grinding?

820
00:31:08,700 --> 00:31:10,635
It's a bisque
made with an entire lobster tail.

821
00:31:10,702 --> 00:31:11,970
A bisque.

822
00:31:12,036 --> 00:31:13,104
What's that? The heat is high.

823
00:31:13,171 --> 00:31:14,205
-Sung-ju!
-Yes?

824
00:31:14,272 --> 00:31:16,975
The butter is melting over high heat,
so try that!

825
00:31:17,041 --> 00:31:18,676
-What now?
-The butter.

826
00:31:18,743 --> 00:31:20,411
-That butter?
-The heat is high.

827
00:31:20,478 --> 00:31:22,380
This one? It looks burning hot.

828
00:31:22,447 --> 00:31:23,715
WANT SOME?

829
00:31:23,781 --> 00:31:25,350
What is this for?

830
00:31:25,416 --> 00:31:26,584
I'm making croutons.

831
00:31:26,651 --> 00:31:27,952
Croutons?

832
00:31:28,019 --> 00:31:29,387
-Croutons?
-He's using lots of butter.

833
00:31:29,454 --> 00:31:32,490
It's much better when cooked
in burnt butter. It's like sesame oil.

834
00:31:32,557 --> 00:31:35,293
He's creating different textures

835
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:37,629
to add variety to his soups.

836
00:31:38,129 --> 00:31:41,099
I don't see anything
that resembles soup on this side.

837
00:31:41,165 --> 00:31:42,767
-This is ready, so try that.
-What's this?

838
00:31:42,834 --> 00:31:43,668
That's the potage.

839
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:46,571
-Let me try the potage!
-The potage.

840
00:31:46,638 --> 00:31:48,573
-The potage.
-This is important.

841
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,341
-The potage.
-The potage.

842
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:53,378
Is it delicious enough
to awaken the Sleeping Beauty?

843
00:31:53,444 --> 00:31:55,413
It's absolutely delicious!

844
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:56,948
For the Sleeping Beauty!

845
00:31:57,015 --> 00:31:58,616
It'll wake her up right away!

846
00:31:58,683 --> 00:32:00,885
-Will she?
-She'll wake up immediately!

847
00:32:00,952 --> 00:32:02,620
It's the wake-up soup.

848
00:32:02,687 --> 00:32:05,556
-The wake-up soup?
-This is so good.

849
00:32:05,623 --> 00:32:07,025
-No, that's…
-What's this?

850
00:32:07,091 --> 00:32:08,760
Strawberry coulis, the dessert.

851
00:32:08,826 --> 00:32:11,129
Let me try the dessert too!

852
00:32:11,195 --> 00:32:12,797
YUM

853
00:32:12,864 --> 00:32:14,799
The dessert… Oh, man!

854
00:32:14,866 --> 00:32:16,801
WHAT IS IT?

855
00:32:16,868 --> 00:32:17,735
The dessert.

856
00:32:17,802 --> 00:32:19,537
This will wake her up too!

857
00:32:20,271 --> 00:32:22,140
RISE AND SHINE

858
00:32:22,206 --> 00:32:23,374
What's this?

859
00:32:23,441 --> 00:32:25,710
-He's done with this too.
-Quickly.

860
00:32:25,777 --> 00:32:27,512
-Is this the bisque?
-Yes.

861
00:32:27,578 --> 00:32:29,080
Made with ground up lobster.

862
00:32:29,147 --> 00:32:30,381
-Ground lobster.
-It must be good.

863
00:32:30,448 --> 00:32:32,517
WHAT'S THIS SOUP LIKE?

864
00:32:32,583 --> 00:32:33,751
CURIOUS

865
00:32:33,818 --> 00:32:35,520
I think Jong-won will win!

866
00:32:35,586 --> 00:32:38,256
HAPPY, SAD

867
00:32:38,323 --> 00:32:40,391
JONG-WON'S FANS SHOUT FOR JOY

868
00:32:40,959 --> 00:32:42,961
I CAN'T WATCH THIS…
SAM'S CHILDREN FANS BECOME BLUE

869
00:32:43,027 --> 00:32:44,929
This is important.

870
00:32:45,496 --> 00:32:46,597
How much time do I have?

871
00:32:46,664 --> 00:32:48,066
Make sure the meat comes in strong!

872
00:32:48,132 --> 00:32:49,968
You really don't have much time.

873
00:32:50,034 --> 00:32:51,636
-The steak.
-You don't have time.

874
00:32:51,703 --> 00:32:53,705
Sam, you need to step it up!

875
00:32:53,771 --> 00:32:57,175
All three of his soups were delicious!

876
00:32:57,241 --> 00:32:59,043
Try Sam's potato soup too.

877
00:32:59,110 --> 00:33:00,645
-Try this.
-Is it ready?

878
00:33:00,712 --> 00:33:02,780
Sam's potato soup!

879
00:33:03,381 --> 00:33:07,819
Can he stop him?

880
00:33:09,053 --> 00:33:10,388
Not quite yet!

881
00:33:10,955 --> 00:33:11,823
Why not?

882
00:33:11,889 --> 00:33:13,658
-It's a bit bland, Sam.
-It's bland?

883
00:33:13,725 --> 00:33:15,827
I don't like heavily seasoned food.

884
00:33:15,893 --> 00:33:18,396
Wait, she doesn't like
heavily seasoned dishes.

885
00:33:18,463 --> 00:33:20,698
-Okay.
-So nothing too salty.

886
00:33:20,765 --> 00:33:22,033
On the side.

887
00:33:22,100 --> 00:33:23,568
I don't think the steak will be ready.

888
00:33:23,634 --> 00:33:25,069
Is that enough to cook the steak?

889
00:33:25,136 --> 00:33:26,037
You need some oil.

890
00:33:26,104 --> 00:33:28,906
-Wait, is that…
-It won't cook without it.

891
00:33:28,973 --> 00:33:30,775
-Add more oil.
-Give me a moment.

892
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:32,777
-You need oil.
-Add lots of oil.

893
00:33:32,844 --> 00:33:34,078
No, add butter!

894
00:33:34,145 --> 00:33:35,513
Add butter too!

895
00:33:35,580 --> 00:33:37,448
Drop that butter inside!

896
00:33:37,515 --> 00:33:38,516
Drop the butter!

897
00:33:38,583 --> 00:33:39,784
-Wait.
-Add it and make it good!

898
00:33:39,851 --> 00:33:40,918
Hey, you need to be quiet.

899
00:33:41,953 --> 00:33:43,588
Put melted butter in!

900
00:33:43,654 --> 00:33:44,655
THIS IS CULINARY BOOT CAMP

901
00:33:44,722 --> 00:33:46,858
-Wait.
-He's focused.

902
00:33:46,924 --> 00:33:49,060
Things seem hectic for Sam.

903
00:33:50,194 --> 00:33:54,432
6. STIR-FRY BUTTON MUSHROOMS WITH
CRUSHED GARLIC, VINEGAR, PEPPER, BUTTER

904
00:33:54,499 --> 00:33:55,633
The heat.

905
00:33:55,700 --> 00:33:56,968
I'm in trouble.

906
00:33:57,035 --> 00:33:59,237
It was a bit bland before.

907
00:33:59,303 --> 00:34:00,471
He says it's bland.

908
00:34:00,538 --> 00:34:04,075
-Add some more salt.
-It won't be easy to beat Jong-won.

909
00:34:04,142 --> 00:34:05,176
Is it fully cooked?

910
00:34:05,243 --> 00:34:06,277
-It is.
-It is?

911
00:34:06,344 --> 00:34:09,981
-It's cooked. The lobster's cooked.
-It's cooked very nicely.

912
00:34:10,048 --> 00:34:11,382
THE LOBSTER GOES INTO A BOWL!

913
00:34:11,983 --> 00:34:14,952
JONG-WON GRABS HIS LOBSTER TOO!

914
00:34:16,387 --> 00:34:18,056
He put it in brown butter.

915
00:34:18,122 --> 00:34:19,757
FINISHING WITH A DASH OF BUTTER

916
00:34:20,324 --> 00:34:22,360
NEXT, SLICING STRAWBERRIES

917
00:34:22,427 --> 00:34:23,895
One minute!

918
00:34:23,961 --> 00:34:27,031
PIPE STRAWBERRY CREAM CHEESE, 10 SECONDS
TOP WITH STRAWBERRIES, 15 SECONDS

919
00:34:27,098 --> 00:34:30,101
-The strawberry soup!
-You have under a minute!

920
00:34:30,168 --> 00:34:33,938
Jong-won's recipes are going smoothly
according to his plan.

921
00:34:34,005 --> 00:34:35,506
"Who's going to stop me?"

922
00:34:35,573 --> 00:34:37,575
-His details.
-He decorates with 40 seconds left?

923
00:34:37,642 --> 00:34:38,709
Forty-three seconds!

924
00:34:38,776 --> 00:34:39,811
-No way.
-Forty-three seconds!

925
00:34:39,877 --> 00:34:41,279
-How amazing.
-He's topping strawberries.

926
00:34:41,345 --> 00:34:43,381
-It looks exquisite!
-That's amazing.

927
00:34:43,448 --> 00:34:45,183
Jong-won puts strawberry pieces

928
00:34:45,249 --> 00:34:46,751
into the bowl!

929
00:34:46,818 --> 00:34:47,819
TIMETABLE

930
00:34:47,885 --> 00:34:49,053
It's shaped like a rose.

931
00:34:49,987 --> 00:34:51,355
POUR STRAWBERRY SOUP, 10 SECONDS

932
00:34:51,422 --> 00:34:54,459
He put that in the middle
and poured the soup on the edge.

933
00:34:54,525 --> 00:34:56,394
So there are two different textures.

934
00:34:56,461 --> 00:34:57,728
Fifteen seconds!

935
00:34:57,795 --> 00:35:01,599
Sam's working on the potato soup again.

936
00:35:01,666 --> 00:35:02,600
One minute!

937
00:35:02,667 --> 00:35:04,602
I guess he's putting it in here. Yes.

938
00:35:04,669 --> 00:35:06,204
-Wait, no?
-No.

939
00:35:06,270 --> 00:35:07,939
-I guess not.
-No?

940
00:35:08,005 --> 00:35:09,540
-It's going in here?
-Yes.

941
00:35:09,607 --> 00:35:12,276
He poured the soup next to the lobster.

942
00:35:14,545 --> 00:35:16,614
TUNA ZUCCHINI ROLL, DONE
BACON POTATO SOUP AND LOBSTER, DONE

943
00:35:16,681 --> 00:35:17,682
This is bad.

944
00:35:17,748 --> 00:35:19,083
LASTLY, THE STEAK!

945
00:35:19,150 --> 00:35:20,818
CHOPPING IT UP TO SERVE IT

946
00:35:20,885 --> 00:35:21,886
WITH BUTTON MUSHROOMS!

947
00:35:21,953 --> 00:35:24,055
Fifteen seconds!

948
00:35:24,856 --> 00:35:25,857
Button mushroom slices.

949
00:35:25,923 --> 00:35:27,892
Nothing is finished yet!

950
00:35:27,959 --> 00:35:29,927
Neither of them are finished
with 15 seconds left!

951
00:35:29,994 --> 00:35:31,295
-Ten seconds!
-Ten!

952
00:35:31,362 --> 00:35:33,030
-Nine. Eight.
-Nine. Eight.

953
00:35:33,097 --> 00:35:34,232
-Seven.
-Seven.

954
00:35:34,298 --> 00:35:35,533
TREMBLING HANDS

955
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:38,169
FINISHING OFF WITH BALSAMIC VINEGAR

956
00:35:38,736 --> 00:35:40,338
JONG-WON ALSO CHOPS LOBSTER

957
00:35:40,838 --> 00:35:41,806
PLATING

958
00:35:42,507 --> 00:35:43,941
TOP WITH A TUILE TO FINISH

959
00:35:44,008 --> 00:35:45,409
-Five. Four.
-Five. Four.

960
00:35:45,476 --> 00:35:46,611
CABBAGE POTAGE

961
00:35:47,612 --> 00:35:48,779
LOBSTER SOUP

962
00:35:48,846 --> 00:35:51,749
-Time's up!
-Your time's up!

963
00:35:51,816 --> 00:35:53,317
Please finish up.

964
00:35:53,384 --> 00:35:56,287
-You cannot cook anymore.
-The end.

965
00:35:56,354 --> 00:35:58,156
Sam rang the bell after Jong-won.

966
00:35:58,222 --> 00:36:00,491
The quality of these dishes
seems way too high

967
00:36:00,558 --> 00:36:02,260
from the start of the year.

968
00:36:02,326 --> 00:36:05,496
It was because she wanted a course meal.

969
00:36:05,563 --> 00:36:07,098
It's tough to make that.

970
00:36:07,165 --> 00:36:09,667
-It was the toughest yet.
-That was really hard.

971
00:36:09,734 --> 00:36:11,402
