-I must've lost my mind.

1212
00:44:58,162 --> 00:45:00,064
It's been a while
since someone cooked for her.

1213
00:45:00,130 --> 00:45:03,067
I was focused on eating my food,
thinking I was here all alone.

1214
00:45:03,133 --> 00:45:05,235
My bad. I'm sorry.

1215
00:45:05,302 --> 00:45:06,704
-It's okay.
-It's not a lot of food,

1216
00:45:06,770 --> 00:45:09,139
so she has to stop before she's satisfied.

1217
00:45:09,206 --> 00:45:10,874
Do you have anything for Ji-tae?

1218
00:45:10,941 --> 00:45:12,843
-No, it's okay.
-I'm really sorry,

1219
00:45:12,910 --> 00:45:15,112
but I only have the soups
without the garnishes.

1220
00:45:15,179 --> 00:45:16,714
-Just the soup?
-Thank you.

1221
00:45:16,780 --> 00:45:17,781
The dessert.

1222
00:45:17,848 --> 00:45:20,584
It's such an honor.

1223
00:45:20,651 --> 00:45:22,619
Are those all three soups Jong-won made?

1224
00:45:22,686 --> 00:45:25,255
Please try Chef Jong-won's soups.
What do you think?

1225
00:45:26,423 --> 00:45:27,658
It makes you want the next one.

1226
00:45:28,225 --> 00:45:31,528
-You must finish it quickly.
-Yes, I'm dying to know.

1227
00:45:31,595 --> 00:45:33,731
That's the French <i>jeon.</i>

1228
00:45:33,797 --> 00:45:35,399
Will it taste good without the lobster?

1229
00:45:35,466 --> 00:45:37,434
This is really good.

1230
00:45:37,501 --> 00:45:38,869
Gosh. It's so good.

1231
00:45:38,936 --> 00:45:41,338
Starting off the new year
with an incredibly hard episode.

1232
00:45:41,405 --> 00:45:44,675
-That was the dessert soup.
-I had briefly lost my mind.

1233
00:45:47,010 --> 00:45:48,445
This is so luxurious.

1234
00:45:48,512 --> 00:45:50,147
It's so good, isn't it?

1235
00:45:50,214 --> 00:45:52,616
He just said the dish was luxurious.

1236
00:45:52,683 --> 00:45:54,585
Next, Chef Sam's dish,

1237
00:45:54,651 --> 00:45:56,453
-the Canine Sampler.
-I see.

1238
00:45:56,520 --> 00:45:59,123
-The Canine Sampler?
-The Canine Sampler?

1239
00:45:59,189 --> 00:46:00,324
The sampler?

1240
00:46:00,390 --> 00:46:01,391
It's too little.

1241
00:46:01,458 --> 00:46:03,327
He tries the steak.

1242
00:46:03,393 --> 00:46:05,729
-The zucchini.
-He's missing out on the tuna.

1243
00:46:05,796 --> 00:46:08,499
-Yes, he didn't get the tuna.
-It was served with the zucchini.

1244
00:46:08,565 --> 00:46:11,135
-The zucchini tastes so good, though.
-Does it?

1245
00:46:11,201 --> 00:46:13,137
-Don't leave her anything next week.
-Right.

1246
00:46:13,203 --> 00:46:15,139
How did he make this flavor?

1247
00:46:15,205 --> 00:46:18,509
-The steak doesn't smell at all.
-No funky smell.

1248
00:46:18,575 --> 00:46:20,577
It won't be easy to choose one.

1249
00:46:20,644 --> 00:46:23,447
What do I do? I really can't choose one.

1250
00:46:23,514 --> 00:46:26,583
But you must give us your choice.

1251
00:46:26,650 --> 00:46:29,419
It's the opening game of 2026.

1252
00:46:29,486 --> 00:46:31,421
Son Jong-won versus Sam Kim.

1253
00:46:31,488 --> 00:46:33,524
The two fought with their course meals.

1254
00:46:33,590 --> 00:46:36,560
<i>Press one to choose Jong-won</i>

1255
00:46:36,627 --> 00:46:38,061
<i>and two to pick Sam.</i>

1256
00:46:39,229 --> 00:46:40,697
Make your decision,

1257
00:46:40,764 --> 00:46:42,666
and press the button!

1258
00:46:43,267 --> 00:46:45,102
-Please!
-"Please"?

1259
00:46:45,903 --> 00:46:47,070
This is so hard.

1260
00:46:47,137 --> 00:46:48,071
She can't choose.

1261
00:46:48,138 --> 00:46:50,274
But the rule of the show

1262
00:46:50,340 --> 00:46:52,810
is that only one chef gets the star.

1263
00:46:52,876 --> 00:46:54,978
You must pick one of the two.

1264
00:46:55,045 --> 00:46:56,580
Ji-tae, you're still working on it?

1265
00:46:57,381 --> 00:46:58,582
It's just that good.

1266
00:46:58,649 --> 00:47:01,285
It's just that good?

1267
00:47:01,351 --> 00:47:02,352
-Both are…
-I'll press it.

1268
00:47:02,419 --> 00:47:03,821
Yes, press it!

1269
00:47:03,887 --> 00:47:05,122
She made her choice.

1270
00:47:05,189 --> 00:47:09,226
And now, let's find out
who became the winner.

1271
00:47:09,293 --> 00:47:12,095
Who did Min-jung choose?

1272
00:47:12,162 --> 00:47:13,964
Did Sam persevere

1273
00:47:14,031 --> 00:47:17,201
after last year's disappointing result
and rise above?

1274
00:47:17,267 --> 00:47:21,305
Or will it be Jong-won,
who's recently been on the rise?

1275
00:47:21,371 --> 00:47:23,640
Min-jung made her choice

1276
00:47:23,707 --> 00:47:26,109
and decided the winner
of the first match of 2026!

1277
00:47:26,176 --> 00:47:28,045
Who is it?

1278
00:47:28,111 --> 00:47:29,613
SON JONG-WON WINS

1279
00:47:30,047 --> 00:47:31,381
CHEF SON JONG-WON'S
SOUP-EATING BEAUTY WINS

1280
00:47:31,448 --> 00:47:33,250
Jong-won wins!

1281
00:47:33,317 --> 00:47:36,453
Jong-won became the winner
of the opening game!

1282
00:47:38,355 --> 00:47:41,191
-Both meals were so delicious,
-I see.

1283
00:47:41,258 --> 00:47:43,360
so it was very hard to choose.

1284
00:47:43,427 --> 00:47:47,130
But Jong-won opened the meal
and closed it too,

1285
00:47:47,197 --> 00:47:49,132
so that was the decisive point.

1286
00:47:49,199 --> 00:47:50,601
But everything was good.

1287
00:47:50,667 --> 00:47:53,103
Eating all six courses
was the best, actually.

1288
00:47:54,238 --> 00:47:56,373
I'm so grateful that you enjoyed the meal,

1289
00:47:56,440 --> 00:47:59,610
and thank you for letting me
start the year off pleasantly.

1290
00:47:59,676 --> 00:48:03,046
Chef Jong-won wins the opening game!

1291
00:48:03,113 --> 00:48:04,815
Please put the star on him.

1292
00:48:04,882 --> 00:48:06,984
And you can hand him the prize too.

1293
00:48:07,050 --> 00:48:08,185
WITH WHISKEY, THE NEW YEAR'S GIFT

1294
00:48:08,252 --> 00:48:10,120
-Congratulations, Jong-won!
-Congratulations!

1295
00:48:10,821 --> 00:48:12,589
He's the winner of the opening game!

1296
00:48:12,656 --> 00:48:14,992
And he gets to take the best whiskey home.

1297
00:48:15,692 --> 00:48:17,728
BREAK BEFORE THE NEXT ROUND

1298
00:48:17,794 --> 00:48:21,265
When I was younger, I was blown away
when I saw my upperclassmen

1299
00:48:21,331 --> 00:48:23,033
holding their cameras.

1300
00:48:23,100 --> 00:48:24,902
That's how I feel right now.

1301
00:48:24,968 --> 00:48:26,570
I suddenly feel like

1302
00:48:26,637 --> 00:48:29,506
I want to become a chef
after seeing all of you.

1303
00:48:29,573 --> 00:48:30,908
You two were so cool.

1304
00:48:30,974 --> 00:48:32,876
Well, it's not too late.

1305
00:48:32,943 --> 00:48:34,778
Chef Sam's meal was so delicious,

1306
00:48:34,845 --> 00:48:36,413
so the difference

1307
00:48:36,480 --> 00:48:39,883
was just about 0.1 points,
no, 0.001 points.

1308
00:48:39,950 --> 00:48:43,987
<i>Let us begin the second cook-off</i>
<i>with Min-jung's ingredients.</i>

1309
00:48:44,054 --> 00:48:46,423
Chef Jung Ho-young,
our dancing villain who's more invested

1310
00:48:46,490 --> 00:48:49,593
-in dancing than cooking.
-The dancing villain?

1311
00:48:49,660 --> 00:48:53,163
He's up against
the villain of <i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>

1312
00:48:53,230 --> 00:48:56,266
who irritates the chefs
with his wicked dishes.

1313
00:48:56,333 --> 00:49:00,637
Our own two villains
are up against each other.

1314
00:49:00,704 --> 00:49:04,708
There's a theory that Ho-young always wins
whenever his dance is received well.

1315
00:49:05,475 --> 00:49:07,377
So in this season,

1316
00:49:07,444 --> 00:49:11,014
I'm going to utilize my friendship
with choreographer Bae Yoon-jeong.

1317
00:49:11,081 --> 00:49:12,816
-Do you know her well?
-I do.

1318
00:49:12,883 --> 00:49:14,818
I'm considering taking private lessons.

1319
00:49:14,885 --> 00:49:16,386
BURNING WITH PASSION

1320
00:49:16,453 --> 00:49:19,890
-You're going that far?
-He wants to take dance lessons

1321
00:49:19,957 --> 00:49:21,725
to bring up his win rate.

1322
00:49:21,792 --> 00:49:24,094
It sounds like
a nice New Year's resolution.

1323
00:49:24,161 --> 00:49:25,829
In the new year,

1324
00:49:25,896 --> 00:49:27,764
I'll study different cooking techniques,

1325
00:49:27,831 --> 00:49:31,234
and I have plans to develop
my own secret recipes…

1326
00:49:31,301 --> 00:49:32,736
-Yes?
-…that bring out more depth.

1327
00:49:32,803 --> 00:49:35,939
-You sound like a chef.
-Did you two switch resolutions?

1328
00:49:36,006 --> 00:49:37,774
I think our resolutions switched.

1329
00:49:38,442 --> 00:49:41,111
You're not a chef,
so you don't have to go that far.

1330
00:49:41,178 --> 00:49:42,646
-Huh?
-The two--

1331
00:49:42,713 --> 00:49:44,281
-The two--
-What's wrong?

1332
00:49:44,348 --> 00:49:46,516
-Dang it. I didn't bring my knife. Wait.
-What's wrong?

1333
00:49:46,583 --> 00:49:48,752
-He forgot his knife.
-He forgot his knife.

1334
00:49:48,819 --> 00:49:51,488
It's all right.
The knife in the studio is all right.

1335
00:49:51,555 --> 00:49:52,589
You didn't bring your knife?

1336
00:49:52,656 --> 00:49:54,324
-I…
-Do you want to borrow mine?

1337
00:49:54,391 --> 00:49:56,493
No, I wouldn't dare. I can't handle it.

1338
00:49:57,060 --> 00:49:58,996
I REFUSE TO USE KNIVES THAT ARE TOO GOOD

1339
00:49:59,062 --> 00:50:01,932
-It's all right.
-But your personal knife is so important.

1340
00:50:01,999 --> 00:50:03,266
How can a chef forget his knife?

1341
00:50:03,333 --> 00:50:04,334
TREATING HIM LIKE A CHEF?

1342
00:50:04,401 --> 00:50:06,670
-I had been studying too hard.
-And he just noticed.

1343
00:50:07,504 --> 00:50:09,606
WEBTOON ARTIST POONG'S INGREDIENTS:
POTATO, BUTTON MUSHROOM, ZUCCHINI

1344
00:50:09,673 --> 00:50:11,675
BROCCOLI, CHERRY TOMATO, TENDERLOIN,
SOEGOGI-MUGUK, BRISKET BROTH, AND MORE

1345
00:50:11,742 --> 00:50:14,044
Webtoon Artist Poong, what are you making?

1346
00:50:14,111 --> 00:50:16,947
Here's the name of the dish
I'll make today.

1347
00:50:17,014 --> 00:50:18,882
F4 Jeongol.

1348
00:50:18,949 --> 00:50:21,118
-F4 Jeongol.
-F4 Jeongol.

1349
00:50:21,685 --> 00:50:22,753
HAHA

1350
00:50:22,819 --> 00:50:25,355
-Are you going to become Gu Jun-poong?
-That's right.

1351
00:50:25,422 --> 00:50:27,424
-Gu Jun-poong?
-Gu Jun-poong?

1352
00:50:27,491 --> 00:50:29,760
The F stands for family,

1353
00:50:29,826 --> 00:50:31,361
and the number 4 for the 4 members.

1354
00:50:31,428 --> 00:50:35,532
So I'm going to make <i>jeongol,</i>
a Korean-style hot pot for the four.

1355
00:50:35,599 --> 00:50:38,835
There's something very important
for households with children.

1356
00:50:38,902 --> 00:50:41,805
It's that the food must be made
to the taste of the youngest child.

1357
00:50:41,872 --> 00:50:43,173
THAT'S TRUE

1358
00:50:43,240 --> 00:50:46,443
-So I have to go low on salt.
-That's right.

1359
00:50:46,510 --> 00:50:48,145
That's the biggest challenge for me,

1360
00:50:48,211 --> 00:50:49,713
so I'll make the <i>jeongol</i>

1361
00:50:49,780 --> 00:50:53,150
in four different vah-riations.

1362
00:50:53,216 --> 00:50:55,419
-Vah-riations?
-Variations.

1363
00:50:55,485 --> 00:50:57,154
-Vah-riations?
-All it takes is a few sauces.

1364
00:50:57,220 --> 00:50:59,589
I thought you said a barista.
You meant variations.

1365
00:50:59,656 --> 00:51:02,125
-They'll add new variations.
-That's it.

1366
00:51:02,192 --> 00:51:03,894
Back in the day,
we all pronounced it "vah-riations."

1367
00:51:05,595 --> 00:51:07,431
You made the fridge owner laugh.

1368
00:51:07,497 --> 00:51:08,632
GU JUN-POONG IS TOO FUNNY

1369
00:51:08,698 --> 00:51:09,833
-Goodness gracious.
-Anyway.

1370
00:51:09,900 --> 00:51:12,836
For BH, who loves Korean food,

1371
00:51:12,903 --> 00:51:14,538
it can turn into a nice <i>gukbap,</i> rice soup,

1372
00:51:14,604 --> 00:51:15,939
just like gochujang-<i>jjigae.</i>

1373
00:51:16,006 --> 00:51:19,609
The sauce for MJ will turn it into a stew,

1374
00:51:19,676 --> 00:51:21,378
a flavor found in Western cuisine.

1375
00:51:21,445 --> 00:51:23,213
Lastly, when your two children eat this,

1376
00:51:23,280 --> 00:51:25,449
they can enjoy the mildly seasoned soup.

1377
00:51:25,515 --> 00:51:29,352
So in total,
it'll turn into four different dishes.

1378
00:51:29,419 --> 00:51:31,788
That was why you named it F4 Jeongol.

1379
00:51:32,722 --> 00:51:34,724
CHEF HO-YOUNG'S INGREDIENTS:
SMALL ANCHOVIES, ZUCCHINI, BUTTON MUSHROOM

1380
00:51:34,791 --> 00:51:36,793
CHERRY TOMATO, MUKEUNJI, STRIP LOIN,
UDON SOY SAUCE, BALSAMIC VINEGAR, AND MORE

1381
00:51:37,360 --> 00:51:40,597
Up against him is Chef Ho-young.
What are you making?

1382
00:51:40,664 --> 00:51:42,966
It's something
the entire family will love,

1383
00:51:43,033 --> 00:51:44,601
fresh homemade pasta.

1384
00:51:44,668 --> 00:51:47,671
I'll bring out the strengths
of Korean and Western cuisine

1385
00:51:47,737 --> 00:51:50,140
and use lots of anchovies for the pasta,

1386
00:51:50,207 --> 00:51:51,675
as well as some <i>mukeunji.</i>

1387
00:51:51,741 --> 00:51:53,577
I thought pasta might not be enough,

1388
00:51:53,643 --> 00:51:56,613
so I'll roll up some beef with veggies

1389
00:51:56,680 --> 00:51:58,381
and make grilled beef veggie rolls.

1390
00:51:59,149 --> 00:52:02,752
I want to make a dish
that'll please all four of you.

1391
00:52:03,253 --> 00:52:04,221
GETTING EXCITED

1392
00:52:04,287 --> 00:52:05,989
His approach is a bit different.

1393
00:52:06,056 --> 00:52:08,091
Then let us begin the 15 minutes

1394
00:52:08,158 --> 00:52:09,459
for the second round.

1395
00:52:09,526 --> 00:52:12,095
Here to become Gu Jun-poong of the show

1396
00:52:12,162 --> 00:52:15,499
and seize the heart of Min-jung's family,
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong is up.

1397
00:52:15,565 --> 00:52:18,135
This man wants to take one shot
and win both in dancing and cooking,

1398
00:52:18,201 --> 00:52:19,669
the dancer of the show,

1399
00:52:19,736 --> 00:52:22,405
Chef Jung Ho-young,
is up for the challenge as well.

1400
00:52:22,472 --> 00:52:26,710
Who will become the honorary cook
for Min-jung and Byung-hun's family?

1401
00:52:26,776 --> 00:52:29,412
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1402
00:52:29,479 --> 00:52:30,313
Let's go!

1403
00:52:31,448 --> 00:52:33,150
THE DANCING VILLAIN
VS CHEF & MY FRIDGE VILLAIN

1404
00:52:33,750 --> 00:52:35,452
1. BOIL SMALL ANCHOVIES

1405
00:52:36,119 --> 00:52:37,120
He's making pasta dough.

1406
00:52:37,187 --> 00:52:38,421
FLOUR, EGG

1407
00:52:38,488 --> 00:52:40,390
-Is he mixing those?
-Fresh pasta.

1408
00:52:40,457 --> 00:52:43,160
He mixed flour and an egg.

1409
00:52:43,226 --> 00:52:44,661
That's pasta dough.

1410
00:52:44,728 --> 00:52:46,263
He's making pasta.

1411
00:52:46,329 --> 00:52:47,297
Wow.

1412
00:52:47,364 --> 00:52:50,834
-His dish is called Homemade Attraction.
-Yes.

1413
00:52:50,901 --> 00:52:51,968
Fresh homemade pasta.

1414
00:52:52,536 --> 00:52:53,870
UP AGAINST HIM IS F4 JEONGOL

1415
00:52:53,937 --> 00:52:55,338
-What's that?
-<i>Soegogi-muguk.</i>

1416
00:52:55,405 --> 00:52:57,707
-<i>Soegogi-muguk,</i> beef and radish soup.
-And brisket broth.

1417
00:52:57,774 --> 00:53:00,343
He's using brisket broth too.

1418
00:53:00,410 --> 00:53:02,145
-It already looks good.
-He's mixing two broths.

1419
00:53:02,212 --> 00:53:03,980
-It already does.
-It must be.

1420
00:53:04,548 --> 00:53:08,018
HE'S GOOD WITH THE BASIC KITCHEN KNIFE TOO

1421
00:53:08,518 --> 00:53:10,854
2. POUR HOT WATER
OVER THINLY SLICED POTATO

1422
00:53:10,921 --> 00:53:13,890
Poong sliced the potato,
and he'll probably microwave it.

1423
00:53:13,957 --> 00:53:16,927
-Huh?
-Sam did that before.

1424
00:53:16,993 --> 00:53:19,062
-I'm copying him right away.
-Right away.

1425
00:53:19,129 --> 00:53:21,398
NO ONE ON THE SHOW LEARNS
AS QUICKLY AS HE DOES

1426
00:53:21,464 --> 00:53:24,201
And a zucchini.

1427
00:53:24,935 --> 00:53:27,437
Sam also did that with the zucchini.

1428
00:53:27,504 --> 00:53:28,505
Copied right away.

1429
00:53:28,572 --> 00:53:29,906
Copied right away.

1430
00:53:29,973 --> 00:53:31,041
Mushrooms too.

1431
00:53:31,107 --> 00:53:33,677
He's mostly prepping the vegetables.

1432
00:53:35,512 --> 00:53:36,913
CHOPPING QUICKLY

1433
00:53:36,980 --> 00:53:38,515
He slams it like a drum.

1434
00:53:38,582 --> 00:53:40,717
The pieces look almost too big.

1435
00:53:40,784 --> 00:53:41,985
His knife skills

1436
00:53:42,052 --> 00:53:43,653
have worsened compared to last year.

1437
00:53:44,955 --> 00:53:46,223
Because the knife is lighter,

1438
00:53:46,289 --> 00:53:48,091
I think he's moving
much faster than usual.

1439
00:53:48,158 --> 00:53:49,192
Is that so?

1440
00:53:49,259 --> 00:53:52,062
Is it because that isn't
his usual Chinese kitchen knife?

1441
00:53:52,128 --> 00:53:53,163
I guess so.

1442
00:53:53,230 --> 00:53:54,598
It's much lighter.

1443
00:53:54,664 --> 00:53:55,932
3. MAKE GREEN ONION OIL

1444
00:53:56,333 --> 00:53:57,934
CHOPPED ONION, INTO A BLENDER

1445
00:53:58,001 --> 00:54:00,370
-He planned to grind it.
-He was going to grind it anyway.

1446
00:54:00,437 --> 00:54:02,739
THE REASON FOR QUICK AND SLOPPY(?) CUTS

1447
00:54:04,207 --> 00:54:05,275
Damn it.

1448
00:54:05,342 --> 00:54:07,177
-Damn it.
-The mushrooms weren't cut.

1449
00:54:07,244 --> 00:54:08,245
What?

1450
00:54:08,645 --> 00:54:09,579
THE 2ND TRY

1451
00:54:09,646 --> 00:54:10,580
It didn't get chopped?

1452
00:54:10,647 --> 00:54:12,315
The mushrooms remained whole.

1453
00:54:13,483 --> 00:54:14,651
He didn't put the blade in.

1454
00:54:15,118 --> 00:54:16,152
WHY AM I STUCK HERE?

1455
00:54:16,219 --> 00:54:17,254
Dang it.

1456
00:54:17,320 --> 00:54:19,155
He didn't put the blade in?

1457
00:54:19,222 --> 00:54:20,957
He didn't stick it on properly.

1458
00:54:21,491 --> 00:54:24,628
-What's wrong with this?
-It should stick right inside.

1459
00:54:25,195 --> 00:54:26,029
THE 4TH TRY!

1460
00:54:27,130 --> 00:54:29,833
Why is he trying
harder and harder when he cooks?

1461
00:54:29,899 --> 00:54:31,601
-He's so serious.
-Isn't he too serious?

1462
00:54:31,668 --> 00:54:33,136
Damn it!

1463
00:54:33,703 --> 00:54:35,839
GIVES UP QUICKLY

1464
00:54:37,107 --> 00:54:39,175
He's throwing in slapstick comedy
into his recipe.

1465
00:54:39,242 --> 00:54:41,611
-It didn't grind the onion either.
-It's the same.

1466
00:54:41,678 --> 00:54:42,746
It's okay.

1467
00:54:42,812 --> 00:54:44,748
He says it's okay.

1468
00:54:45,315 --> 00:54:47,183
This is for Min-jung's sauce.

1469
00:54:48,218 --> 00:54:51,554
It doesn't seem like
Poong is off to a great start.

1470
00:54:52,188 --> 00:54:55,458
He always begins like this,
but his dishes always turn out well.

1471
00:54:55,525 --> 00:54:56,626
-Right?
-It may be a plan.

1472
00:54:56,693 --> 00:54:57,861
He should pull out

1473
00:54:57,927 --> 00:55:01,264
-the piece of green-colored onion.
-Pull it out. It's too big.

1474
00:55:01,331 --> 00:55:03,033
He's adding different textures.

1475
00:55:04,534 --> 00:55:06,536
He must be throwing in diverse textures.

1476
00:55:06,603 --> 00:55:09,072
-A dish that adults would love?
-Sure.

1477
00:55:11,708 --> 00:55:13,476
JAPANESE CUISINE IS ALL ABOUT THE KNIFE!

1478
00:55:14,210 --> 00:55:15,345
AND I'M GOOD WITH IT

1479
00:55:15,412 --> 00:55:16,846
I'm a bit worried about Poong.

1480
00:55:16,913 --> 00:55:18,315
Chef Ho-young is very detailed.

1481
00:55:18,381 --> 00:55:19,215
-He is.
-Yes.

1482
00:55:19,282 --> 00:55:20,684
4. SLICE CHERRY TOMATOES, GARLIC CLOVES

1483
00:55:20,750 --> 00:55:22,485
The process is always much better
for the chefs.

1484
00:55:23,053 --> 00:55:24,187
Wow.

1485
00:55:24,254 --> 00:55:26,890
-Is that <i>mukeunji?</i>
-It is.

1486
00:55:26,956 --> 00:55:29,559
-The <i>mukeunji</i> her mother-in-law made.
-Yes.

1487
00:55:29,626 --> 00:55:32,329
Director Park Chan-wook wanted to start
a business with that <i>mukeunji!</i>

1488
00:55:32,395 --> 00:55:33,997
And kimchi? Wow.

1489
00:55:34,531 --> 00:55:35,832
STRIP LOIN

1490
00:55:35,899 --> 00:55:37,600
HE POUNDS!

1491
00:55:37,667 --> 00:55:41,237
Chef Ho-young pounds on the meat
to make it easier for the children to eat.

1492
00:55:41,304 --> 00:55:43,139
It'll be much easier to eat.

1493
00:55:43,940 --> 00:55:46,543
THE STRIP LOIN IS NOW AS THIN AS PAPER!

1494
00:55:46,943 --> 00:55:48,445
SEASON WITH SALT AND PEPPER

1495
00:55:49,546 --> 00:55:51,648
A BIT OF SALT ON THE VEGGIES TOO

1496
00:55:52,182 --> 00:55:55,185
FINISHED GRILLING
ZUCCHINI AND BUTTON MUSHROOMS

1497
00:55:56,619 --> 00:55:58,355
RED PEPPER POWDER

1498
00:55:58,421 --> 00:56:00,390
Hey, the chili oil.

1499
00:56:00,457 --> 00:56:02,325
-Chili oil.
-For a baby?

1500
00:56:02,392 --> 00:56:04,160
No, it's for one of the adults.

1501
00:56:04,227 --> 00:56:05,862
It's for BH.

1502
00:56:06,162 --> 00:56:08,631
CHILI OIL FOR THE F1, BH

1503
00:56:08,698 --> 00:56:09,532
Ground pepper.

1504
00:56:09,599 --> 00:56:11,501
Ground pepper.

1505
00:56:11,568 --> 00:56:13,570
-He grabs… Whoa!
-Whoa!

1506
00:56:13,636 --> 00:56:16,272
-Isn't that too much?
-It's too spicy for kids!

1507
00:56:16,339 --> 00:56:18,541
-Can the baby eat that?
-It's not… It's not for the baby!

1508
00:56:18,608 --> 00:56:19,776
It must be for the adults.

1509
00:56:19,843 --> 00:56:21,378
-You're right.
-I thought so.

1510
00:56:21,444 --> 00:56:23,747
-It's not for the baby, is it?
-It's not.

1511
00:56:23,813 --> 00:56:25,014
I'm glad.

1512
00:56:25,081 --> 00:56:28,451
There's a French mushroom dish
made with ground mushrooms

1513
00:56:28,518 --> 00:56:29,786
called duxelles.

1514
00:56:29,853 --> 00:56:31,154
I think he's making that.

1515
00:56:31,221 --> 00:56:32,455
Are you making that?

1516
00:56:32,522 --> 00:56:33,390
Huh? What now?

1517
00:56:35,258 --> 00:56:36,192
What now?

1518
00:56:36,259 --> 00:56:38,361
What you're doing now
is a French method of cooking.

1519
00:56:38,428 --> 00:56:39,362
It is?

1520
00:56:39,796 --> 00:56:42,766
A TIGER KNOWS HOW TO HUNT WITHOUT LEARNING

1521
00:56:42,832 --> 00:56:45,001
-You had no idea?
-I didn't know.

1522
00:56:45,068 --> 00:56:46,870
-How did he think of that?
-He's a genius.

1523
00:56:47,670 --> 00:56:48,505
GULP

1524
00:56:50,140 --> 00:56:51,474
Are you okay?

1525
00:56:51,541 --> 00:56:54,744
-He must be allergic.
-The ground pepper must've reached him.

1526
00:56:54,811 --> 00:56:56,079
Ji-tae begins to sneeze.

1527
00:56:56,780 --> 00:56:58,581
-My mouth was watering.
-The ground pepper.

1528
00:56:58,648 --> 00:56:59,849
You were swallowing?

1529
00:56:59,916 --> 00:57:01,785
I'm sorry. I stuffed myself alone.

1530
00:57:01,851 --> 00:57:04,287
He must've choked after his mouth watered.

1531
00:57:04,354 --> 00:57:05,422
I WANT SOME

1532
00:57:05,488 --> 00:57:07,357
Chef Ho-young makes the beef roll.

1533
00:57:07,424 --> 00:57:09,058
I see. He's rolling the beef?

1534
00:57:09,125 --> 00:57:10,360
He's adding tomatoes,

1535
00:57:10,427 --> 00:57:12,028
-zucchini, and mushrooms.
-With the veggies.

1536
00:57:12,095 --> 00:57:14,130
He's rolling the zucchini with beef?

1537
00:57:14,197 --> 00:57:16,266
-It's so healthy.
-It must be very good for you.

1538
00:57:16,332 --> 00:57:18,635
Chef Ho-young puts
the beef roll in a frying pan.

1539
00:57:18,701 --> 00:57:20,503
He didn't use too much oil
for the children.

1540
00:57:20,570 --> 00:57:21,738
A DASH OF OLIVE OIL

1541
00:57:21,805 --> 00:57:22,906
So considerate.

1542
00:57:22,972 --> 00:57:23,840
Gosh.

1543
00:57:23,907 --> 00:57:25,041
That's my master.

1544
00:57:25,108 --> 00:57:26,342
It's a dish for everyone.

1545
00:57:26,409 --> 00:57:28,912
I think he's making the noodles,
fresh homemade pasta.

1546
00:57:29,679 --> 00:57:30,980
WORKING THE DOUGH

1547
00:57:33,049 --> 00:57:34,517
He mainly makes Japanese cuisine,

1548
00:57:34,584 --> 00:57:37,520
so the way he kneads the dough
is different from the traditional way.

1549
00:57:38,988 --> 00:57:42,225
-Is it different from Western cuisine?
-And the way he rolls it out too.

1550
00:57:43,059 --> 00:57:46,362
THE EXPERT JAPANESE CHEF
FIRST FLATTENS IT WITH HIS HANDS

1551
00:57:46,429 --> 00:57:48,198
AND THEN USES A ROLLING PIN

1552
00:57:48,264 --> 00:57:51,100
-He's making it like udon.
-You're right.

1553
00:57:51,167 --> 00:57:52,769
-It's more like udon.
-I see.

1554
00:57:52,836 --> 00:57:54,204
Are you making udon?

1555
00:57:54,270 --> 00:57:56,039
-It's pasta.
-You're making pasta?

1556
00:57:56,105 --> 00:57:57,106
AWW

1557
00:57:57,173 --> 00:57:58,341
It's pasta!

1558
00:57:58,408 --> 00:57:59,742
It's like udon made with an egg.

1559
00:57:59,809 --> 00:58:01,044
-Egg udon.
-It's egg udon.

1560
00:58:01,110 --> 00:58:03,213
-I didn't even use a drop of water.
-Wait.

1561
00:58:03,279 --> 00:58:06,516
Udon suits him better,
so people keep saying it's udon.

1562
00:58:06,583 --> 00:58:07,584
Exactly.

1563
00:58:07,650 --> 00:58:08,985
It's not udon, is it?

1564
00:58:09,052 --> 00:58:11,654
-It's pasta.
-He's making pasta!

1565
00:58:11,721 --> 00:58:12,922
Excuse me, Mr. Jung Udon.

1566
00:58:12,989 --> 00:58:15,058
-"Mr. Jung Udon"?
-Mr. Jung Udon.

1567
00:58:15,124 --> 00:58:17,093
-Yes?
-It's udon, isn't it?

1568
00:58:17,160 --> 00:58:19,195
-It's pasta.
-It's pasta.

1569
00:58:19,262 --> 00:58:20,563
He's Mr. Jung Pasta.

1570
00:58:20,630 --> 00:58:21,664
He didn't fall for it.

1571
00:58:21,731 --> 00:58:24,200
How can he make fresh pasta?

1572
00:58:25,201 --> 00:58:26,636
POONG USES A ZUCCHINI TOO

1573
00:58:27,203 --> 00:58:29,105
What's with the size difference?

1574
00:58:29,172 --> 00:58:30,573
IS THAT THE PROPER WAY TO CHOP?

1575
00:58:31,107 --> 00:58:34,010
-Look at the messy shapes.
-He just slams the knife on the board.

1576
00:58:35,245 --> 00:58:38,248
Chef Ho-young is making one dish
for the entire family to enjoy,

1577
00:58:38,314 --> 00:58:41,851
whereas Webtoon Artist Poong is making
different sauces for the same dish.

1578
00:58:41,918 --> 00:58:43,152
MEAT BROTH INTO THE SAUCE!

1579
00:58:43,219 --> 00:58:44,554
Wow.

1580
00:58:45,922 --> 00:58:47,524
Hey, what's that?

1581
00:58:47,590 --> 00:58:49,192
Is that truffle butter?

1582
00:58:49,259 --> 00:58:50,660
-It is.
-Is it?

1583
00:58:51,127 --> 00:58:52,695
BUTTON MUSHROOMS + TRUFFLE BUTTER
= MJ'S SAUCE

1584
00:58:52,762 --> 00:58:54,731
Min-jung will love that.

1585
00:58:54,797 --> 00:58:56,065
I do like truffles.

1586
00:58:56,132 --> 00:58:57,600
It smells so good.

1587
00:58:57,667 --> 00:59:00,637
Why does it smell like a kitchen
at a French restaurant?

1588
00:59:00,703 --> 00:59:02,639
It smells like L'Amant Secret.

1589
00:59:02,705 --> 00:59:03,606
Does it?

1590
00:59:03,673 --> 00:59:06,075
-It smells French.
-Was it the truffle butter?

1591
00:59:06,142 --> 00:59:10,914
He also throws in some broccoli.

1592
00:59:10,980 --> 00:59:12,982
Do people use broccoli to make <i>jeongol?</i>

1593
00:59:13,049 --> 00:59:15,885
It's hard to tell
which one is for BH, which is for MJ,

1594
00:59:15,952 --> 00:59:17,620
-and the one for the kids.
-Is that <i>malatang?</i>

1595
00:59:17,687 --> 00:59:20,356
-Yes, it's like <i>malatang.</i>
-Are you making <i>malatang?</i>

1596
00:59:20,423 --> 00:59:21,758
It's like a Chinese hot pot.

1597
00:59:21,824 --> 00:59:22,992
-Is it?
-No!

1598
00:59:23,059 --> 00:59:24,527
-It's like HaiDiLao.
-It's not like that.

1599
00:59:25,194 --> 00:59:26,029
A DEEP BREATH

1600
00:59:26,796 --> 00:59:28,197
TURNING THE STRIP LOIN ROLL OVER!

1601
00:59:28,264 --> 00:59:29,198
My gosh.

1602
00:59:30,600 --> 00:59:31,634
Wow.

1603
00:59:32,201 --> 00:59:36,005
Chef Ho-young begins to cut the pasta.

1604
00:59:36,072 --> 00:59:37,674
-He's cutting the noodles.
-The pasta.

1605
00:59:37,740 --> 00:59:40,009
7. CHOP THE DOUGH AND MAKE PASTA

1606
00:59:40,076 --> 00:59:43,112
-It looks like udon. So evenly cut.
-It's udon.

1607
00:59:43,179 --> 00:59:44,681
He made fettuccine.

1608
00:59:45,815 --> 00:59:47,116
Wow.

1609
00:59:47,750 --> 00:59:49,285
REMOVING THE PARBOILED ANCHOVIES

1610
00:59:49,986 --> 00:59:52,121
8. ADD UDON SOY SAUCE
INTO THE ANCHOVY BROTH

1611
00:59:52,188 --> 00:59:54,490
You have 6 minutes and 30 seconds.

1612
00:59:54,557 --> 00:59:57,427
-You don't have much time.
-Really? 6 minutes and 30 seconds?

1613
00:59:57,493 --> 00:59:58,795
Six minutes and twenty seconds.

1614
00:59:58,861 --> 01:00:00,229
The time is flying by today.

1615
01:00:00,296 --> 01:00:01,364
Why is it flying by?

1616
01:00:01,431 --> 01:00:04,000
You have 6 minutes and 30 seconds.

1617
01:00:04,067 --> 01:00:05,935
GREEN ONION AND ONION FOR BH

1618
01:00:06,002 --> 01:00:06,936
Six minutes and twenty seconds.

1619
01:00:07,003 --> 01:00:07,937
TWO BLADES?

1620
01:00:08,004 --> 01:00:10,306
Six minutes and twenty seconds?
Time is flying by.

1621
01:00:10,840 --> 01:00:11,808
Wait.

1622
01:00:11,874 --> 01:00:14,277
Where's the lid?

1623
01:00:14,344 --> 01:00:16,346
He wants to grind something,
but can't find the lid.

1624
01:00:16,412 --> 01:00:18,948
-No, the blades.
-Poong can't find the lid!

1625
01:00:19,015 --> 01:00:21,150
-It's right there!
-The lid! He can't find the lid!

1626
01:00:21,217 --> 01:00:22,952
-The blades. Okay.
-He loses a lot of time!

1627
01:00:23,019 --> 01:00:24,854
No, the blades were in here.

1628
01:00:24,921 --> 01:00:26,689
-It was in here!
-It was inside.

1629
01:00:26,756 --> 01:00:28,891
-The blades were inside.
-No!

1630
01:00:28,958 --> 01:00:30,994
He just lost about 30 seconds.

1631
01:00:31,060 --> 01:00:32,395
Six minutes left.

1632
01:00:32,462 --> 01:00:33,796
READY TO MIX WITH CHILI OIL

1633
01:00:33,863 --> 01:00:34,831
Hurry up, Master.

1634
01:00:34,897 --> 01:00:37,233
Ho-young continues to cook smoothly.

1635
01:00:38,234 --> 01:00:40,403
-Isn't this cooked enough?
-The pasta is ready.

1636
01:00:40,470 --> 01:00:41,638
Already?

1637
01:00:41,704 --> 01:00:44,474
-Isn't it too early?
-Already? I doubt it's cooked.

1638
01:00:44,540 --> 01:00:47,143
-It's not cooked yet.
-It's not?

1639
01:00:48,177 --> 01:00:50,947
-Okay.
-You can't ask him. Decide it yourself.

1640
01:00:52,382 --> 01:00:54,550
GRABBING THE STEAMED POTATO
FROM THE MICROWAVE!

1641
01:00:54,617 --> 01:00:56,085
It's hot!

1642
01:00:56,152 --> 01:00:58,821
-I can handle it. I'm a cook!
-The potato is ready.

1643
01:00:58,888 --> 01:01:00,723
-His pasta is ready.
-Flour?

1644
01:01:02,125 --> 01:01:04,127
-What's that?
-He's doing that instead of making roux.

1645
01:01:04,193 --> 01:01:05,528
Who is that for?

1646
01:01:05,595 --> 01:01:08,631
You don't have to make the sauce
for their dog.

1647
01:01:10,833 --> 01:01:14,270
It's only for the four human members,
not the animal companion.

1648
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:16,039
-What's that?
-Jung-hwan!

1649
01:01:16,105 --> 01:01:17,407
Please report from the kitchen.

1650
01:01:17,473 --> 01:01:19,642
-You have to try that.
-It's the interim check.

1651
01:01:19,709 --> 01:01:20,677
You have to try it.

1652
01:01:20,743 --> 01:01:22,245
Please find out what that is.

1653
01:01:22,311 --> 01:01:23,746
I'm curious too.

1654
01:01:23,813 --> 01:01:26,015
-May I try this, Poong?
-Sure.

1655
01:01:26,082 --> 01:01:27,183
But it won't be good.

1656
01:01:27,984 --> 01:01:29,585
What do you mean it won't be good?

1657
01:01:29,652 --> 01:01:31,921
I'll mix it with the broth later.

1658
01:01:31,988 --> 01:01:34,090
Please try that sauce.

1659
01:01:34,157 --> 01:01:35,058
IT GIVES HIM A BIG FROWN

1660
01:01:35,124 --> 01:01:37,260
-Stop frowning and try it.
-Eat it.

1661
01:01:37,326 --> 01:01:40,163
So? Is he Gu Jun-poong or Grim Poong?

1662
01:01:42,598 --> 01:01:44,267
Which one is it?

1663
01:01:44,333 --> 01:01:46,335
Is he Gu Jun-poong or Grim Poong?

1664
01:01:46,402 --> 01:01:47,570
He's Grim Poong!

1665
01:01:47,637 --> 01:01:49,005
-No!
-It's still grim.

1666
01:01:49,072 --> 01:01:50,473
You have to save it.

1667
01:01:50,540 --> 01:01:52,008
Yes, you must save it.

1668
01:01:52,075 --> 01:01:54,410
-He needs to add some seasoning.
-I guess so.

1669
01:01:54,477 --> 01:01:57,146
-He adds some more broth.
-It tastes flat.

1670
01:01:57,213 --> 01:01:58,748
It's nothing much so far.

1671
01:01:58,815 --> 01:02:00,717
-Not so far.
-Not yet.

1672
01:02:00,783 --> 01:02:02,752
-What's that with the garlic slices?
-Kimchi.

1673
01:02:02,819 --> 01:02:04,721
-I see. Kimchi.
-And anchovy broth.

1674
01:02:04,787 --> 01:02:06,189
-Anchovy broth.
-Wow.

1675
01:02:06,255 --> 01:02:07,523
Shouldn't you stir-fry the pasta?

1676
01:02:07,590 --> 01:02:08,991
Yes, I'll do that now.

1677
01:02:09,726 --> 01:02:12,261
WOW

1678
01:02:12,328 --> 01:02:14,430
Both fridge owners are impressed.

1679
01:02:14,497 --> 01:02:17,433
-Wow.
-It looks like Ho-young will win.

1680
01:02:17,500 --> 01:02:18,901
10. MIX ANCHOVY SOY BROTH
WITH GARLIC AND MUKEUNJI

1681
01:02:18,968 --> 01:02:20,002
Are you making <i>yaki udon?</i>

1682
01:02:20,069 --> 01:02:21,771
-<i>Yaki udon.</i>
-It's pasta!

1683
01:02:21,838 --> 01:02:24,474
-Ho-young's face brightens up.
-It's not udon, is it?

1684
01:02:24,540 --> 01:02:25,775
-Is that pasta?
-It's pasta.

1685
01:02:25,842 --> 01:02:26,743
+GROUND PEPPER

1686
01:02:27,376 --> 01:02:28,678
Isn't that <i>yakisoba?</i>

1687
01:02:29,312 --> 01:02:30,580
I'm telling you, it's pasta!

1688
01:02:30,646 --> 01:02:31,614
MUST KEEP EXPLAINING

1689
01:02:32,348 --> 01:02:34,684
OKAY, FINE, IT'S PASTA

1690
01:02:35,384 --> 01:02:37,220
It looks a lot like Japanese udon.

1691
01:02:37,286 --> 01:02:38,888
-<i>Yakisoba.</i>
-Try some.

1692
01:02:38,955 --> 01:02:40,490
Is it pasta or udon?

1693
01:02:40,556 --> 01:02:42,925
Do you feel the attraction or not?

1694
01:02:42,992 --> 01:02:46,729
Now, is it magnetic? Is it udon or pasta?

1695
01:02:46,796 --> 01:02:48,397
-Udon.
-What's it like?

1696
01:02:48,464 --> 01:02:49,866
Do you feel the attraction?

1697
01:02:50,967 --> 01:02:52,702
-I do!
-You do?

1698
01:02:52,769 --> 01:02:55,671
It has the texture of pasta.

1699
01:02:55,738 --> 01:02:56,973
It's pasta.

1700
01:02:57,039 --> 01:02:59,342
-And butter. That looks good.
-It's still

1701
01:02:59,408 --> 01:03:02,211
-a bit bland, probably for the kids.
-Is it?

1702
01:03:02,278 --> 01:03:04,213
-What did you just throw in?
-Anchovies.

1703
01:03:04,280 --> 01:03:05,581
-Anchovies?
-Yes, anchovies.

1704
01:03:05,882 --> 01:03:06,916
SERVES THE DISH RIGHT AWAY

1705
01:03:06,983 --> 01:03:09,519
Ho-young begins to plate the dish.

1706
01:03:09,585 --> 01:03:12,321
PASTA ON ONE SIDE

1707
01:03:12,388 --> 01:03:14,557
NEXT, THE NICELY GRILLED STRIP LOIN ROLL

1708
01:03:15,124 --> 01:03:17,660
12. COAT THE ROLL WITH BALSAMIC VINEGAR
AND CHOP INTO BITE SIZES

1709
01:03:17,727 --> 01:03:19,195
Ho-young is almost done.

1710
01:03:19,262 --> 01:03:22,765
Chef Ho-young begins to plate his dish.

1711
01:03:22,832 --> 01:03:23,866
Balsamic vinegar.

1712
01:03:25,368 --> 01:03:26,335
That's hot!

1713
01:03:26,969 --> 01:03:29,038
9. MIX STEAMED POTATO WITH STARCH AND SALT

1714
01:03:29,105 --> 01:03:30,540
WORKING

1715
01:03:30,606 --> 01:03:31,874
Wait.

1716
01:03:31,941 --> 01:03:34,377
-Is that <i>ongsimi</i>, potato dough?
-He's making <i>ongsimi.</i>

1717
01:03:34,443 --> 01:03:38,481
He mixed the potato he cooked
in the microwave with some starch.

1718
01:03:38,548 --> 01:03:41,417
He made that with potatoes?

1719
01:03:41,484 --> 01:03:42,885
Man.

1720
01:03:42,952 --> 01:03:44,320
Wait!

1721
01:03:44,387 --> 01:03:47,123
Poong suddenly seasons the meat.
Why are you doing this?

1722
01:03:47,190 --> 01:03:49,392
It's the right time. It's fine.

1723
01:03:49,458 --> 01:03:51,527
You only have a minute.
Are you serving beef tartare?

1724
01:03:51,594 --> 01:03:52,895
Is that the case?

1725
01:03:52,962 --> 01:03:54,931
I hope it's not raw. One minute!

1726
01:03:54,997 --> 01:03:57,900
-Raw beef isn't good for kids.
-One minute!

1727
01:03:57,967 --> 01:03:59,402
-One minute!
-One minute.

1728
01:03:59,468 --> 01:04:02,004
-In there?
-In the pot.

1729
01:04:02,071 --> 01:04:04,106
He's cooking it in the pot.

1730
01:04:04,173 --> 01:04:05,808
It'll only take 30 seconds to cook.

1731
01:04:05,875 --> 01:04:07,109
Thirty seconds are enough.

1732
01:04:07,476 --> 01:04:09,345
IT LOOKS LIKE A SOLID JEONGOL

1733
01:04:09,412 --> 01:04:10,847
The <i>jeongol</i> looks solid.

1734
01:04:10,913 --> 01:04:12,348
The heat went off.

1735
01:04:12,415 --> 01:04:13,749
He turned it off.

1736
01:04:13,816 --> 01:04:14,750
It was intentional.

1737
01:04:14,817 --> 01:04:16,185
Will the meat still cook?

1738
01:04:16,252 --> 01:04:18,454
-Thirty seconds!
-What now?

1739
01:04:18,521 --> 01:04:20,189
Ho-young is almost done.

1740
01:04:20,623 --> 01:04:22,024
20 SECONDS LEFT!

1741
01:04:22,358 --> 01:04:25,795
TRUFFLE BUTTER ON STRIP LOIN ROLL

1742
01:04:25,862 --> 01:04:27,663
Fifteen seconds!

1743
01:04:27,730 --> 01:04:29,198
+SUGAR
ONLY THE CHILI OIL SAUCE REMAINS!

1744
01:04:29,265 --> 01:04:30,366
+RED PEPPER POWDER

1745
01:04:32,368 --> 01:04:33,803
Fifteen seconds!

1746
01:04:34,837 --> 01:04:36,572
PARMESAN ON THE PASTA

1747
01:04:36,639 --> 01:04:37,640
Time's almost up.

1748
01:04:37,707 --> 01:04:39,775
-Five. Four.
-Four.

1749
01:04:39,842 --> 01:04:41,344
FINISHING WITH OLIVE OIL!

1750
01:04:41,410 --> 01:04:42,845
Time's almost up.

1751
01:04:43,179 --> 01:04:44,914
THE SOY SAUCE…

1752
01:04:44,981 --> 01:04:46,415
SPILLS OUT!

1753
01:04:47,049 --> 01:04:50,119
SHOULD I POUR THE WHOLE THING IN? OR NO?

1754
01:04:53,089 --> 01:04:55,191
THE CHILI OIL SAUCE IS FINISHED
FOR THE F1, BH

1755
01:04:55,258 --> 01:04:56,459
What are you doing?

1756
01:04:58,594 --> 01:04:59,729
That's time.

1757
01:04:59,795 --> 01:05:01,697
-Ho-young is done!
-Chef Ho-young is done!

1758
01:05:02,431 --> 01:05:03,733
-And Poong?
-You must finish too.

1759
01:05:03,799 --> 01:05:05,568
-Ring the bell.
-Yes, I should do that.

1760
01:05:06,435 --> 01:05:07,703
STEALTHY

1761
01:05:11,540 --> 01:05:12,975
WHY DOES THE LAW EXIST IF SORRY IS ENOUGH?

1762
01:05:13,042 --> 01:05:15,211
What did you throw in as you walked?

1763
01:05:15,278 --> 01:05:17,313
It's my eyes.
I'll need reading glasses soon.

1764
01:05:17,380 --> 01:05:18,247
Why scoop it back out?

1765
01:05:18,314 --> 01:05:19,682
-He added too much.
-It was too much.

1766
01:05:23,085 --> 01:05:23,920
KIM POONG FINISHES F4 JEONGOL

1767
01:05:23,986 --> 01:05:25,688
Poong finishes too.

1768
01:05:27,290 --> 01:05:28,124
Poong finishes too.

1769
01:05:28,190 --> 01:05:29,392
Serve it as is.

1770
01:05:29,458 --> 01:05:32,495
-You rang the bell, so serve them.
-I hope the soup tastes okay.

1771
01:05:32,561 --> 01:05:34,563
Put it on the table.
It's a part of the dish.

1772
01:05:36,098 --> 01:05:37,767
Right. I forgot to grab rice. Dang it.

1773
01:05:37,833 --> 01:05:39,101
-He forgot the rice?
-Rice.

1774
01:05:39,168 --> 01:05:40,903
-You're serving it like this?
-One second.

1775
01:05:40,970 --> 01:05:42,238
You're serving the whole pot?

1776
01:05:42,305 --> 01:05:44,807
And the whole frying pan?

1777
01:05:44,874 --> 01:05:46,542
You couldn't serve it on a dish?

1778
01:05:47,543 --> 01:05:49,879
THAT'S KIM POONG FOR YA!

1779
01:05:49,946 --> 01:05:54,383
And two more dishes were made
just for Min-jung.

1780
01:05:54,450 --> 01:05:56,419
Poong served lots of things on the table.

1781
01:05:56,485 --> 01:05:58,354
Why is the green onion there?

1782
01:05:58,421 --> 01:06:00,723
-Isn't it a part of the dish?
-No, it's not.

1783
01:06:00,790 --> 01:06:01,791
It's not.

1784
01:06:01,857 --> 01:06:04,060
What do you take me for?

1785
01:06:04,126 --> 01:06:06,729
The camera crew already filmed
the insert shot!

1786
01:06:07,296 --> 01:06:09,398
FILMED THE INSERT SHOT
WITHOUT AN INCH OF DOUBT

1787
01:06:09,465 --> 01:06:11,067
I know I can be crazy,

1788
01:06:11,133 --> 01:06:13,636
but I wouldn't serve
half-finished green onions.

1789
01:06:13,703 --> 01:06:16,572
Wait a second. You said it was F4 Jeongol.

1790
01:06:16,639 --> 01:06:18,341
This is F1, this is F2,

1791
01:06:18,407 --> 01:06:20,643
-Yeah?
-so you're missing two.

1792
01:06:20,710 --> 01:06:23,479
I meant to serve
the kids' portion in a tiny bowl.

1793
01:06:23,546 --> 01:06:26,315
-What about the insert shot?
-What's this, then?

1794
01:06:26,382 --> 01:06:27,750
-What is it?
-It's nothing.

1795
01:06:27,817 --> 01:06:28,784
Did you use it already?

1796
01:06:29,185 --> 01:06:31,053
NO ONE QUESTIONED IT
BECAUSE POONG HAS A LONG HISTORY

1797
01:06:31,120 --> 01:06:34,357
-It wasn't her style.
-These are for the kids.

1798
01:06:34,423 --> 01:06:35,524
F1 and F2.

1799
01:06:35,591 --> 01:06:38,828
Mickey and Minnie Mouse utensils
are the kick for this dish.

1800
01:06:38,894 --> 01:06:39,762
He prepared utensils.

1801
01:06:39,829 --> 01:06:42,832
So these are F3 and F4.

1802
01:06:42,898 --> 01:06:45,368
-F3 gets soy sauce.
-Right. Soy sauce.

1803
01:06:45,434 --> 01:06:48,738
And unfortunately, F4 gets air.

1804
01:06:48,804 --> 01:06:50,806
-Air.
-All right, then.

1805
01:06:50,873 --> 01:06:52,908
We thought the green onion
was a part of your dish.

1806
01:06:52,975 --> 01:06:54,176
-I know me, but…
-I was wrong.

1807
01:06:54,243 --> 01:06:56,879
Chef Ho-young finished first.

1808
01:06:57,513 --> 01:07:01,817
HOMEMADE FRESH PASTA
WITH MUKEUNJI AND ANCHOVIES

1809
01:07:03,219 --> 01:07:05,988
BEEF ROLL FULL OF VEGGIES

1810
01:07:06,889 --> 01:07:10,192
CHEF JUNG HO-YOUNG'S HOMEMADE ATTRACTION

1811
01:07:10,259 --> 01:07:13,662
I've had some food and come to my senses,

1812
01:07:13,729 --> 01:07:15,364
so should I set half of this aside?

1813
01:07:15,965 --> 01:07:17,666
He has more over there.

1814
01:07:17,733 --> 01:07:19,769
-He has more.
-He prepared more.

1815
01:07:19,835 --> 01:07:21,270
This time, there's more food.

1816
01:07:21,337 --> 01:07:22,972
I wasn't in my right mind.

1817
01:07:23,039 --> 01:07:25,441
-I was hungry.
-And entranced by the course meals.

1818
01:07:25,508 --> 01:07:28,944
Please try the dishes
as you think of your family.

1819
01:07:29,011 --> 01:07:30,379
I've never seen anchovy pasta.

1820
01:07:30,446 --> 01:07:32,748
It would be great for the kids' bones.

1821
01:07:32,815 --> 01:07:36,285
He thinks your family
will all love this dish.

1822
01:07:36,352 --> 01:07:39,321
-Stir-fried anchovies are great for kids.
-And for adults.

1823
01:07:39,388 --> 01:07:41,557
Of course, the mother must love it.

1824
01:07:41,824 --> 01:07:42,892
MMM

1825
01:07:42,958 --> 01:07:46,262
It tastes a bit different
from the kind of flavor I imagined.

1826
01:07:46,328 --> 01:07:47,630
Unlike my imagination,

1827
01:07:47,696 --> 01:07:49,565
it's cleaner and toastier.

1828
01:07:49,965 --> 01:07:51,100
WOW

1829
01:07:51,167 --> 01:07:52,168
For the children.

1830
01:07:52,234 --> 01:07:54,670
I thought it'd be richer.

1831
01:07:54,737 --> 01:07:56,539
It had a strong cheese smell,

1832
01:07:56,605 --> 01:07:59,742
so I thought it'd be rich,
but it's clean and toasty.

1833
01:07:59,809 --> 01:08:02,011
How are the anchovies not fishy?

1834
01:08:02,078 --> 01:08:04,313
-<i>I parboiled them first.</i>
-<i>You parboiled them.</i>

1835
01:08:04,380 --> 01:08:06,615
<i>It makes them softer and less fishy.</i>

1836
01:08:06,682 --> 01:08:08,584
That's his secret.

1837
01:08:08,651 --> 01:08:10,920
He's good with fish.

1838
01:08:10,986 --> 01:08:12,121
He always delivers.

1839
01:08:12,288 --> 01:08:13,222
SPINNING

1840
01:08:13,289 --> 01:08:15,257
Yes, Ho-young.

1841
01:08:15,324 --> 01:08:17,126
He's always good with fish dishes.

1842
01:08:17,193 --> 01:08:20,196
But BH doesn't like Western cuisine.

1843
01:08:20,262 --> 01:08:21,597
-No.
-He's into Korean food.

1844
01:08:21,664 --> 01:08:24,333
That's why I added
some stir-fried <i>mukeunji.</i>

1845
01:08:24,400 --> 01:08:28,170
That's what I'm tasting right now.

1846
01:08:28,237 --> 01:08:29,805
It must be closer to Korean food.

1847
01:08:29,872 --> 01:08:32,241
I kept wondering
what this savory flavor was,

1848
01:08:32,308 --> 01:08:34,009
and there was <i>mukeunji </i>in here.

1849
01:08:34,076 --> 01:08:35,411
ANOTHER BITE

1850
01:08:35,478 --> 01:08:37,480
That's for your husband.

1851
01:08:37,546 --> 01:08:38,881
MMM

1852
01:08:38,948 --> 01:08:40,349
Does it also taste Korean?

1853
01:08:40,416 --> 01:08:42,151
-It does.
-Will BH love it too?

1854
01:08:42,218 --> 01:08:43,152
Yes.

1855
01:08:43,219 --> 01:08:46,288
It looks like his pasta passed.

1856
01:08:46,355 --> 01:08:47,556
He's great with fish dishes.

1857
01:08:47,623 --> 01:08:48,924
AGAIN, SHE'S BUSY EATING

1858
01:08:48,991 --> 01:08:50,626
This is good.

1859
01:08:50,693 --> 01:08:52,294
She's enjoying it like a bar snack.

1860
01:08:52,361 --> 01:08:54,463
I said I was partially full
and wouldn't eat more, but I did.

1861
01:08:54,897 --> 01:08:56,198
ENJOY IT AS MUCH AS YOU LIKE

1862
01:08:56,265 --> 01:08:58,634
And the beef roll. What's inside?

1863
01:08:58,701 --> 01:09:02,471
<i>I rolled it with zucchini,</i>
<i>button mushrooms, and tomatoes.</i>

1864
01:09:02,538 --> 01:09:04,773
I rolled it up
to let the children eat the veggies

1865
01:09:04,840 --> 01:09:06,575
without picking on it.

1866
01:09:07,776 --> 01:09:10,179
-It looks good.
-He rolled up veggies with beef.

1867
01:09:11,213 --> 01:09:12,081
A healthy flavor.

1868
01:09:12,148 --> 01:09:14,316
It must be so nice when the tomato pops.

1869
01:09:15,084 --> 01:09:16,385
This can't taste bad.

1870
01:09:16,752 --> 01:09:17,887
PLEASED

1871
01:09:17,953 --> 01:09:19,622
It's something even kids will enjoy.

1872
01:09:19,688 --> 01:09:23,125
-It's so good.
-Chef Ho-young may get a good result.

1873
01:09:23,192 --> 01:09:25,861
Next, Webtoon Artist Poong's F4 Jeongol.

1874
01:09:27,029 --> 01:09:30,199
A JEONGOL DISH FULL OF MEAT AND VEGGIES

1875
01:09:30,266 --> 01:09:32,334
MUSHROOM SAUCE FOR F2, MJ

1876
01:09:32,401 --> 01:09:35,137
CHILI SAUCE FOR F1, BH
DIFFERENT SAUCES FOR EACH FAMILY MEMBER

1877
01:09:35,638 --> 01:09:37,439
The camera crew already filmed
the insert shot!

1878
01:09:37,506 --> 01:09:38,741
AND THE SAUCE THAT DECEIVED THE CREW

1879
01:09:39,775 --> 01:09:43,279
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S F4 JEONGOL

1880
01:09:43,345 --> 01:09:45,848
There's a whole frying pan out here.

1881
01:09:46,715 --> 01:09:48,350
-Please do understand.
-What's that?

1882
01:09:48,417 --> 01:09:49,652
KIM POONG-STYLE PRESENTATION

1883
01:09:49,718 --> 01:09:53,289
You can serve it on the dish…
Let me do that for you.

1884
01:09:53,355 --> 01:09:54,190
The sauce.

1885
01:09:54,256 --> 01:09:55,724
How can you serve the dish like this?

1886
01:09:56,492 --> 01:09:58,627
It looks like
she's done and about to leave.

1887
01:09:58,961 --> 01:10:01,597
VISUALLY SHOCKING

1888
01:10:01,664 --> 01:10:03,432
It could be good, though.

1889
01:10:03,499 --> 01:10:05,067
Excuse me, I'm sorry to ask.

1890
01:10:05,134 --> 01:10:06,902
-This empty bowl is…
-Excuse me.

1891
01:10:06,969 --> 01:10:08,103
-For the youngest.
-Yes, Minnie.

1892
01:10:08,170 --> 01:10:09,638
-Excuse me.
-Minnie Mouse.

1893
01:10:09,705 --> 01:10:10,539
I'm sorry.

1894
01:10:10,606 --> 01:10:12,541
Will someone please listen to him?

1895
01:10:12,608 --> 01:10:16,512
May I serve the rice?
The children should have some.

1896
01:10:16,579 --> 01:10:18,747
You couldn't serve it in time, though.

1897
01:10:18,814 --> 01:10:20,349
Please leave it out of your decision.

1898
01:10:20,416 --> 01:10:22,418
Also, BH's sauce needs some rice too.

1899
01:10:22,484 --> 01:10:25,020
-It's like <i>gukbap.</i>
-Lots of people needed rice.

1900
01:10:25,087 --> 01:10:27,323
-Should she start with her daughter's?
-The youngest.

1901
01:10:27,389 --> 01:10:28,591
-Yes.
-Right.

1902
01:10:28,657 --> 01:10:31,227
If you like broccoli,
you can try that too. Or tomatoes.

1903
01:10:31,293 --> 01:10:34,530
It does look like baby food, I guess.

1904
01:10:34,597 --> 01:10:36,899
-There are lots of veggies in here, so…
-Yes.

1905
01:10:38,334 --> 01:10:40,135
It's seasoned for the youngest child.

1906
01:10:41,403 --> 01:10:43,239
-It's good.
-It is?

1907
01:10:43,305 --> 01:10:44,373
Wait.

1908
01:10:44,440 --> 01:10:45,708
-Is it?
-It's an emergency.

1909
01:10:45,774 --> 01:10:48,310
I don't think you need rice with this.

1910
01:10:48,377 --> 01:10:51,614
The potato plays a role
and makes it like a Korean potato soup.

1911
01:10:51,680 --> 01:10:53,649
-You're right. It's like soup.
-Not bad.

1912
01:10:53,716 --> 01:10:56,885
The potato began to fall apart

1913
01:10:56,952 --> 01:10:59,455
-and became like <i>gamja-guk.</i>
-Yes.

1914
01:10:59,521 --> 01:11:02,258
-It's like that.
-I see.

1915
01:11:02,324 --> 01:11:03,325
It's good.

1916
01:11:04,493 --> 01:11:05,594
Wait.

1917
01:11:05,661 --> 01:11:06,929
-The soup base…
-The youngest, pass.

1918
01:11:06,996 --> 01:11:09,331
It's good for the baby.
A pass for the youngest.

1919
01:11:09,398 --> 01:11:13,135
And Jun-hu can dip the meat
in the soy sauce, right?

1920
01:11:13,202 --> 01:11:16,538
-Yes, a little more soy sauce.
-Some soy sauce for the son.

1921
01:11:18,674 --> 01:11:20,209
-Right.
-It sounds good.

1922
01:11:20,276 --> 01:11:22,745
She doesn't seem too impressed
by this one.

1923
01:11:24,213 --> 01:11:26,482
Is this regular soy sauce?

1924
01:11:26,548 --> 01:11:27,783
It's the soy sauce for eggs.

1925
01:11:27,850 --> 01:11:29,918
A STORE-BOUGHT SOY SAUCE FOR EGGS

1926
01:11:29,985 --> 01:11:31,654
-He didn't make it himself.
-Right.

1927
01:11:31,720 --> 01:11:33,455
It's from a factory.

1928
01:11:33,522 --> 01:11:36,091
She puts the bowl down right away.

1929
01:11:36,158 --> 01:11:38,394
-And next.
-Next, MJ's… Min-jung's sauce.

1930
01:11:38,460 --> 01:11:41,830
Put the veggies, meat,
and potatoes into the bowl.

1931
01:11:41,897 --> 01:11:43,966
-This sauce.
-But don't put too much soup in there,

1932
01:11:44,033 --> 01:11:45,167
-and mix it.
-It's MJ's sauce?

1933
01:11:45,234 --> 01:11:49,271
Wasn't there something about this sauce?

1934
01:11:49,338 --> 01:11:51,140
-Try it.
-It was a bit too flat for me.

1935
01:11:51,206 --> 01:11:53,409
-That made him Grim Poong.
-Grim Poong.

1936
01:11:53,475 --> 01:11:56,378
-That's for the mother.
-What is it?

1937
01:11:56,445 --> 01:11:57,279
Hmm?

1938
01:11:57,346 --> 01:11:58,781
-Hmm?
-What's it like?

1939
01:11:58,847 --> 01:12:00,482
Her eyes became huge.

1940
01:12:00,549 --> 01:12:02,351
-Hmm?
-Huh?

1941
01:12:02,418 --> 01:12:03,319
-It hit her.
-What's this?

1942
01:12:03,385 --> 01:12:05,254
What is it? Is it good?

1943
01:12:05,321 --> 01:12:07,489
I really don't want to be convinced.

1944
01:12:07,556 --> 01:12:09,491
-Is it good?
-Yes, it's good.

1945
01:12:09,558 --> 01:12:11,226
-What is this?
-What is this?

1946
01:12:11,293 --> 01:12:12,961
Kim Poong works his magic.

1947
01:12:13,028 --> 01:12:14,430
Kim Poong's magic.

1948
01:12:14,496 --> 01:12:15,564
It has already begun.

1949
01:12:15,631 --> 01:12:17,132
Ho-young looks gloomy.

1950
01:12:17,199 --> 01:12:21,070
<i>There's a French mushroom dish recipe</i>
<i>using stir-fried ground button mushrooms.</i>

1951
01:12:21,136 --> 01:12:22,471
<i>So it's French?</i>

1952
01:12:22,538 --> 01:12:25,207
-<i>He added truffle butter.</i>
-<i>Truffle butter.</i>

1953
01:12:25,274 --> 01:12:28,277
That's why it tastes so rich.

1954
01:12:29,244 --> 01:12:30,446
How can that be good?

1955
01:12:30,512 --> 01:12:33,382
-He added something else at the end.
-How is that good?

1956
01:12:33,449 --> 01:12:37,453
He poured in chicken stock
just before he finished.

1957
01:12:37,753 --> 01:12:38,954
A SPOON OF MAGIC

1958
01:12:39,021 --> 01:12:40,022
Was that the secret?

1959
01:12:40,089 --> 01:12:41,724
But it didn't end there.

1960
01:12:41,790 --> 01:12:44,026
He put in too much,
so he had to scoop some out.

1961
01:12:44,093 --> 01:12:46,628
-If he didn't, it would've been bad.
-However,

1962
01:12:46,695 --> 01:12:49,031
it's not the kind of flavor
that's only made with chicken stock.

1963
01:12:49,765 --> 01:12:50,599
It must have depth.

1964
01:12:50,666 --> 01:12:52,134
I wasn't sure about Jun-hu's soy sauce,

1965
01:12:52,201 --> 01:12:54,803
but this one hit me hard.

1966
01:12:54,870 --> 01:12:57,539
-I can change the soy sauce.
-Well, the mother is pleased.

1967
01:12:57,606 --> 01:12:59,675
You got lots of points
from the mom's sauce.

1968
01:12:59,742 --> 01:13:01,410
-The last one, for BH.
-For BH.

1969
01:13:01,477 --> 01:13:04,179
-Do I have to add rice here?
-You need rice for BH's sauce.

1970
01:13:04,246 --> 01:13:06,014
Otherwise, you wouldn't get
the right texture.

1971
01:13:06,081 --> 01:13:07,816
-He loves Korean food.
-Yes.

1972
01:13:07,883 --> 01:13:09,918
You can pour in lots of soup
into that one.

1973
01:13:09,985 --> 01:13:12,988
-Lots of soup? Because it's a bit…
-Like <i>gukbap.</i>

1974
01:13:13,055 --> 01:13:15,524
-Right. Like <i>gukbap.</i>
-Yes, like Korean cuisine.

1975
01:13:15,591 --> 01:13:18,293
-It's like a course meal.
-All right, now.

1976
01:13:18,360 --> 01:13:20,329
This one is for the dad.

1977
01:13:20,396 --> 01:13:21,997
-The last one.
-Try it with some rice.

1978
01:13:22,064 --> 01:13:23,132
Is it like <i>yukgaejang?</i>

1979
01:13:23,966 --> 01:13:26,535
-The dad has to like this one.
-BH.

1980
01:13:28,203 --> 01:13:29,304
-Huh?
-What?

1981
01:13:29,371 --> 01:13:31,740
It's the kind of flavor
every guy will love.

1982
01:13:31,807 --> 01:13:33,642
-I see.
-Hey, wait.

1983
01:13:33,709 --> 01:13:36,645
-It's an emergency, Master.
-A <i>gukbap</i> any man would love.

1984
01:13:36,712 --> 01:13:39,014
It must taste like <i>haejang-guk.</i>

1985
01:13:39,915 --> 01:13:43,819
It must be different
when she mixes rice with the soup.

1986
01:13:43,886 --> 01:13:45,754
Yes, it tastes like <i>yukgaejang.</i>

1987
01:13:45,821 --> 01:13:47,222
-It seemed like it.
-It's like <i>yukgaejang.</i>

1988
01:13:47,289 --> 01:13:48,757
It's meat broth and chili oil.

1989
01:13:48,824 --> 01:13:50,526
The more her face brightens up,

1990
01:13:50,592 --> 01:13:52,995
the more Chef Ho-young's face turns gray.

1991
01:13:53,262 --> 01:13:54,096
HAGGARD

1992
01:13:54,163 --> 01:13:55,998
-Look at him.
-It's an emergency.

1993
01:13:56,064 --> 01:13:58,934
Well, it's now time to choose.

1994
01:13:59,001 --> 01:13:59,968
I wonder who it'll be.

1995
01:14:00,035 --> 01:14:03,839
You must decide
who'll take the second star

1996
01:14:03,906 --> 01:14:05,240
of the year 2026.

1997
01:14:05,307 --> 01:14:07,443
<i>Press one for Jung Ho-young</i>

1998
01:14:07,509 --> 01:14:09,011
<i>and two for Kim Poong.</i>

1999
01:14:10,179 --> 01:14:11,613
Gosh.

2000
01:14:11,680 --> 01:14:12,681
This is hard.

2001
01:14:12,748 --> 01:14:14,883
-Will Ho-young lose?
-It's hard?

2002
01:14:14,950 --> 01:14:16,685
It became a tough decision.

2003
01:14:16,752 --> 01:14:17,886
-I'm nervous.
-This had its charms.

2004
01:14:17,953 --> 01:14:19,621
Ho-young expected to cruise to victory,

2005
01:14:19,688 --> 01:14:21,557
-I don't know anymore.
-but he can't be sure now.

2006
01:14:21,623 --> 01:14:24,560
When she first saw it,
she thought she should give it to her dog.

2007
01:14:24,960 --> 01:14:26,094
UNEXPECTEDLY CHARMING

2008
01:14:26,161 --> 01:14:27,896
But the situation has changed.

2009
01:14:28,764 --> 01:14:30,732
Press one for Ho-young, two for Poong!

2010
01:14:30,799 --> 01:14:32,868
-I pressed the button.
-She did.

2011
01:14:32,935 --> 01:14:34,503
It was a tough decision.

2012
01:14:34,570 --> 01:14:36,939
Let's find out the result.

2013
01:14:37,005 --> 01:14:37,973
THE RESULT

2014
01:14:39,241 --> 01:14:41,176
They were to cook for Min-jung's family,

2015
01:14:41,243 --> 01:14:43,045
one dish for all four members.

2016
01:14:43,111 --> 01:14:44,580
Is Poong the winner?

2017
01:14:44,646 --> 01:14:46,281
Or is it Ho-young?

2018
01:14:46,348 --> 01:14:49,852
Did Poong make a last-minute stop
to Ho-young's rise to victory?

2019
01:14:49,918 --> 01:14:51,253
Let's find out

2020
01:14:51,320 --> 01:14:52,554
her decision!

2021
01:14:52,621 --> 01:14:53,956
Who did Min-jung choose?

2022
01:14:54,022 --> 01:14:55,190
JUNG HO-YOUNG WINS

2023
01:14:55,257 --> 01:14:56,692
It was Ho-young!

2024
01:14:56,758 --> 01:14:59,161
CHEF JUNG HO-YOUNG'S
HOMEMADE ATTRACTION WINS

2025
01:14:59,228 --> 01:15:01,129
Jung Ho-young wins!

2026
01:15:01,196 --> 01:15:04,066
She chose Ho-young.

2027
01:15:04,132 --> 01:15:05,734
You were a bit torn toward the end.

2028
01:15:05,801 --> 01:15:09,338
<i>Mukeunji</i> was the kick for this dish.

2029
01:15:09,938 --> 01:15:13,675
He made it with anchovies,
but it wasn't fishy, just delicious.

2030
01:15:13,742 --> 01:15:17,045
I think my children will enjoy it,
thinking it's cheese pasta.

2031
01:15:17,112 --> 01:15:18,847
-Yes.
-On top of that,

2032
01:15:18,914 --> 01:15:22,851
adults can enjoy it without the greasiness
with a little more <i>mukeunji</i> on top.

2033
01:15:22,918 --> 01:15:25,053
That was why I chose this dish.

2034
01:15:25,120 --> 01:15:27,723
But this was really captivating too,

2035
01:15:27,789 --> 01:15:29,725
so I was quite torn.

2036
01:15:29,791 --> 01:15:34,429
It would've been harder to decide
if he had served it with rice.

2037
01:15:34,496 --> 01:15:36,632
It's a shame that he forgot to grab it.

2038
01:15:36,698 --> 01:15:39,434
That was the decisive move.

2039
01:15:39,501 --> 01:15:42,971
Please put the star on Chef Ho-young.

2040
01:15:43,038 --> 01:15:44,172
That's great.

2041
01:15:44,239 --> 01:15:46,308
And a bottle of the best whiskey.

2042
01:15:46,375 --> 01:15:47,676
Congratulations.

2043
01:15:48,243 --> 01:15:51,580
-Ho-young takes his first victory!
-Whiskey!

2044
01:15:54,016 --> 01:15:56,518
We're here with a full-time professor
who teaches at a university.

2045
01:15:56,585 --> 01:15:58,320
I only have 15 minutes.

2046
01:15:58,387 --> 01:15:59,788
-What?
-You have lots of powders.

2047
01:15:59,855 --> 01:16:00,756
This is another powder.

2048
01:16:00,822 --> 01:16:01,890
A fridge full of powder.

2049
01:16:01,957 --> 01:16:02,958
That's for my immunity.

2050
01:16:03,025 --> 01:16:03,959
Most of my meals are clean.

2051
01:16:04,026 --> 01:16:05,360
I just like to drink it.

2052
01:16:05,427 --> 01:16:06,929
Are you not allowed to cook on campus?

2053
01:16:06,995 --> 01:16:07,996
I'm not allowed to use heat.

2054
01:16:08,063 --> 01:16:09,331
Then how do you make your food?

2055
01:16:09,398 --> 01:16:11,333
Please use 15 minutes
to cook without using heat.

2056
01:16:11,400 --> 01:16:13,235
It sounds like the finals.

2057
01:16:13,302 --> 01:16:15,437
You couldn't have a knife on campus,
so I also won't use one.

2058
01:16:15,704 --> 01:16:16,772
HE FOUND A HOPEFUL ASPIRANT

2059
01:16:16,838 --> 01:16:17,873
He's parboiling seafood.

2060
01:16:17,940 --> 01:16:19,408
That's how he's cooking those?

2061
01:16:19,474 --> 01:16:21,109
It looks like
microwaves will be busy today.

2062
01:16:21,443 --> 01:16:22,878
PROFESSOR, I'M ALSO GOOD
AT SPRINKLING SALT

2063
01:16:23,178 --> 01:16:24,479
PROFESSOR YOO IS GREATLY PLEASED

2064
01:16:24,546 --> 01:16:26,214
This is a new assignment.

2065
01:16:26,281 --> 01:16:27,816
-<i>Make a healthy dish.</i>
-<i>Make a healthy dish.</i>

2066
01:16:27,883 --> 01:16:29,184
She's at the top of her game.

2067
01:16:29,251 --> 01:16:31,486
-It looks so healthy.
-It already seems healthy.

2068
01:16:31,553 --> 01:16:33,221
-He's using that much butter?
-Wait.

2069
01:16:33,288 --> 01:16:34,756
How is that healthy?

2070
01:16:34,823 --> 01:16:35,891
It'll give you high cholesterol.

2071
01:16:35,958 --> 01:16:36,959
No, it's so healthy,

2072
01:16:37,025 --> 01:16:37,859
and the portion is huge.

2073
01:16:38,327 --> 01:16:39,561
PROBLEM COMPREHENSION: F

2074
01:16:39,628 --> 01:16:41,496
What's it like? Both chefs are desperate.

2075
01:16:41,563 --> 01:16:42,698
Please, Professor.

2076
01:16:42,764 --> 01:16:44,032
I really need an A!

2077
01:16:44,099 --> 01:16:45,667
Professor, my family is struggling!

2078
01:16:45,968 --> 01:16:47,035
A DESPERATE COMPETITION FOR A GOOD GRADE

2079
01:16:47,302 --> 01:16:49,004
WHICH STUDENT WILL END UP WITH AN A PLUS?

2080
01:16:53,442 --> 01:16:55,243
-Gosh.
-Are you hungover from yesterday?

2081
01:17:06,555 --> 01:17:11,326
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
